63 
64 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], SU2_COMPONENT val_software, bool verb_high) {
65 
66  /*--- Set the case name to the base config file name without extension ---*/
67 
68  caseName = PrintingToolbox::split(string(case_filename),'.')[0];
69 
70  base_config = true;
71 
72  /*--- Store MPI rank and size ---*/
73 
74  rank = SU2_MPI::GetRank();
75  size = SU2_MPI::GetSize();
76 
77  iZone = 0;
78  nZone = 1;
79 
80  Init();
81 
82  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
83 
84  SetConfig_Parsing(case_filename);
85 
86  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
87 
88  SetDefault();
89 
90  /*--- Set number of zone ---*/
91 
92  SetnZone();
93 
94  /*--- Configuration file postprocessing ---*/
95 
96  SetPostprocessing(val_software, iZone, 0);
97 
98  /*--- Configuration file boundaries/markers setting ---*/
99 
100  SetMarkers(val_software);
101 
102  /*--- Configuration file output ---*/
103 
104  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && verb_high)
105  SetOutput(val_software, iZone);
106 
107 }
108 
109 CConfig::CConfig(istream &case_buffer, SU2_COMPONENT val_software, bool verb_high) {

111  base_config = true;
112 
113  iZone = 0;
114  nZone = 1;
115 
116  Init();
117 
118  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
119 
120  SetConfig_Parsing(case_buffer);
121 
122  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
123 
124  SetDefault();
125 
126  /*--- Set number of zone ---*/
127 
128  SetnZone();
129 
130  /*--- Configuration file postprocessing ---*/
131 
132  SetPostprocessing(val_software, iZone, 0);
133 
134  /*--- Configuration file boundaries/markers setting ---*/
135 
136  SetMarkers(val_software);
137 
138  /*--- Configuration file output ---*/
139 
140  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && verb_high)
141  SetOutput(val_software, iZone);
142 
143 }

145 CConfig::CConfig(CConfig* config, char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], SU2_COMPONENT val_software, unsigned short val_iZone, unsigned short val_nZone, bool verb_high) {
146 
147  caseName = config->GetCaseName();
148 
149  unsigned short val_nDim;
150 
151  base_config = false;
152 
153  iZone = val_iZone;
154  nZone = val_nZone;
155 
156  Init();
157 
158  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
159 
160  SetConfig_Parsing(case_filename);
161 
162  /*--- Set default options from base config ---*/
163 
164  SetDefaultFromConfig(config);
165 
166  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
167 
168  SetDefault();
169 
170  /*--- Get the dimension --- */
171 
172  val_nDim = GetnDim(Mesh_FileName, Mesh_FileFormat);
173 
174  /*--- Configuration file postprocessing ---*/
175 
176  SetPostprocessing(val_software, val_iZone, val_nDim);
177 
178  /*--- Configuration file boundaries/markers setting ---*/
179 
180  SetMarkers(val_software);
181 
182  /*--- Configuration file output ---*/
183 
184  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && verb_high)
185  SetOutput(val_software, val_iZone);
186 
187  Multizone_Problem = config->GetMultizone_Problem();
188 
189 }
190 
191 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], SU2_COMPONENT val_software) {
192 
193  /*--- Set the case name to the base config file name without extension ---*/
194 
195  caseName = PrintingToolbox::split(string(case_filename),'.')[0];
196 
197  base_config = true;
198 
199  nZone = 1;
200  iZone = 0;
201 
202  Init();
203 
204  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
205 
206  SetConfig_Parsing(case_filename);
207 
208  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
209 
210  SetDefault();
211 
212  /*--- Set number of zones --- */
213 
214  SetnZone();
215 
216  /*--- Configuration file postprocessing ---*/
217 
218  SetPostprocessing(val_software, 0, 1);
219 
220  /*--- Configuration file boundaries/markers setting ---*/
221 
222  SetMarkers(val_software);
223 
224  /*--- Print the header --- */
225 
226  SetHeader(val_software);
227 
228 }
229 
230 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], CConfig *config) {
231 
232  /*--- Set the case name to the base config file name without extension ---*/
233 
234  caseName = PrintingToolbox::split(string(case_filename),'.')[0];
235 
236  base_config = true;
237 
238  bool runtime_file = false;
239 
240  Init();
241 
242  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
243 
244  runtime_file = SetRunTime_Parsing(case_filename);
245 
246  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
247 
248  SetDefault();
249 
250  /*--- Update original config file ---*/
251 
252  if (runtime_file) {
253  if (all_options.find("TIME_ITER") == all_options.end())
254  config->SetnTime_Iter(nTimeIter);
255  }
256 }

264 void CConfig::Init(){
265 
266  /*--- Store MPI rank and size ---*/
267 
268  rank = SU2_MPI::GetRank();
269  size = SU2_MPI::GetSize();
270 
271  /*--- Initialize pointers to Null---*/
272 
273  SetPointersNull();
274 
275  /*--- Reading config options ---*/
276 
277  SetConfig_Options();
278 
279 }
280 
281 void CConfig::SetMPICommunicator(SU2_MPI::Comm Communicator) {
282 
283  SU2_Communicator = Communicator;
284 
285 }
286 
287 void CConfig::addDoubleOption(const string& name, su2double & option_field, su2double default_value) {
288  // Check if the key is already in the map. If this fails, it is coder error
289  // and not user error, so throw.
290  assert(option_map.find(name) == option_map.end());
291 
292  // Add this option to the list of all the options
293  all_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(name, true));
294 
295  // Create the parser for a su2double option with a reference to the option_field and the desired
296  // default value. This will take the string in the config file, convert it to a su2double, and
297  // place that su2double in the memory location specified by the reference.
298  COptionBase* val = new COptionDouble(name, option_field, default_value);
299 
300  // Create an association between the option name ("CFL") and the parser generated above.
301  // During configuration, the parsing script will get the option name, and use this map
302  // to find how to parse that option.
303  option_map.insert(pair<string, COptionBase *>(name, val));
304 }
305 
306 void CConfig::addStringOption(const string& name, string & option_field, string default_value) {
307 
308  assert(option_map.find(name) == option_map.end());
309  all_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(name, true));
310  COptionBase* val = new COptionString(name, option_field, std::move(default_value));
311  option_map.insert(pair<string, COptionBase *>(name, val));
312 }

349 // enum types work differently than all of the others because there are a small number of valid
350 // string entries for the type. One must also provide a list of all the valid strings of that type.
351 template <class Tenum, class TField>
352 void CConfig::addEnumOption(const string name, TField& option_field, const map<string,Tenum>& enum_map, Tenum default_value) {
353  assert(option_map.find(name) == option_map.end());
354  all_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(name, true));
355  COptionBase* val = new COptionEnum<Tenum, TField>(name, enum_map, option_field, default_value);
356  option_map.insert(pair<string, COptionBase *>(name, val));
357 }
358 
359 // input_size is the number of options read in from the config file
360 template <class Tenum, class TField>
361 void CConfig::addEnumListOption(const string name, unsigned short& input_size, TField*& option_field, const map<string, Tenum>& enum_map) {
362  input_size = 0;
363  assert(option_map.find(name) == option_map.end());
364  all_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(name, true));
365  COptionBase* val = new COptionEnumList<Tenum,TField>(name, enum_map, option_field, input_size);
366  option_map.insert( pair<string, COptionBase*>(name, val) );
367 }

589 
590 unsigned short CConfig::GetnZone(const string& val_mesh_filename, unsigned short val_format) {
591 
592  int nZone = 1; /* Default value if nothing is specified. */
593 
594  switch (val_format) {
595  case SU2: {
596 
597  /*--- Local variables for reading the SU2 file. ---*/
598  string text_line;
599  ifstream mesh_file;
600 
601  /*--- Check if the mesh file can be opened for reading. ---*/
602  mesh_file.open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), ios::in);
603  if (mesh_file.fail())
604  SU2_MPI::Error(string("There is no geometry file called ") + val_mesh_filename,
605  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
606 
607  /*--- Read the SU2 mesh file until the zone data is reached or
608  when it can be decided that it is not present. ---*/
609  while( getline (mesh_file, text_line) ) {
610 
611  /*--- Search for the "NZONE" keyword to see if there are multiple Zones ---*/
612  if(text_line.find ("NZONE=",0) != string::npos) {
613  text_line.erase (0,6); nZone = atoi(text_line.c_str());
614  break;
615  }
616 
617  /*--- If one of the keywords IZONE, NELEM or NPOIN, NMARK is encountered,
618  it can be assumed that the NZONE keyword is not present and the loop
619  can be terminated. ---*/
620  if(text_line.find ("IZONE=",0) != string::npos) break;
621  if(text_line.find ("NELEM=",0) != string::npos) break;
622  if(text_line.find ("NPOIN=",0) != string::npos) break;
623  if(text_line.find ("NMARK=",0) != string::npos) break;
624  }
625 
626  mesh_file.close();
627  break;
628 
629  }
630 
631  case CGNS_GRID: {
632 
633 #ifdef HAVE_CGNS
634 
635  /*--- Local variables which are needed when calling the CGNS mid-level API. ---*/
636 
637  int fn, nbases = 0, nzones = 0, file_type;
638  int cell_dim = 0, phys_dim = 0;
639  char basename[CGNS_STRING_SIZE];
640 
641  /*--- Check whether the supplied file is truly a CGNS file. ---*/
642 
643  if ( cg_is_cgns(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), &file_type) != CG_OK ) {
644  SU2_MPI::Error(val_mesh_filename +
645  string(" was not found or is not a properly formatted CGNS file.\n") +
646  string("Note that SU2 expects unstructured CGNS files in ADF data format."),
647  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
648  }
649 
650  /*--- Open the CGNS file for reading. The value of fn returned
651  is the specific index number for this file and will be
652  repeatedly used in the function calls. ---*/
653 
654  if (cg_open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), CG_MODE_READ, &fn)) cg_error_exit();
655 
656  /*--- Get the number of databases. This is the highest node
657  in the CGNS heirarchy. ---*/
658 
659  if (cg_nbases(fn, &nbases)) cg_error_exit();
660 
661  /*--- Check if there is more than one database. Throw an
662  error if there is because this reader can currently
663  only handle one database. ---*/
664 
665  if ( nbases > 1 ) {
666  SU2_MPI::Error("CGNS reader currently incapable of handling more than 1 database." ,
667  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
668  }
669 
670  /*--- Read the databases. Note that the indexing starts at 1. ---*/
671 
672  for ( int i = 1; i <= nbases; i++ ) {
673 
674  if (cg_base_read(fn, i, basename, &cell_dim, &phys_dim)) cg_error_exit();
675 
676  /*--- Get the number of zones for this base. ---*/
677 
678  if (cg_nzones(fn, i, &nzones)) cg_error_exit();
679 
680  }
681 
682  /*--- Close the CGNS file. ---*/
683 
684  if ( cg_close(fn) ) cg_error_exit();
685 
686  /*--- Set the number of zones as read from the CGNS file ---*/
687 
688  nZone = nzones;
689 
690 #else
691  SU2_MPI::Error(string(" SU2 built without CGNS support. \n") +
692  string(" To use CGNS, build SU2 accordingly."),
693  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
694 #endif
695 
696  break;
697  }
698  case RECTANGLE: {
699  nZone = 1;
700  break;
701  }
702  case BOX: {
703  nZone = 1;
704  break;
705  }
706  }
707 
708  return (unsigned short) nZone;
709 
710 }
711 
712 unsigned short CConfig::GetnDim(const string& val_mesh_filename, unsigned short val_format) {
713 
714  short nDim = -1;
715 
716  switch (val_format) {
717  case SU2: {
718 
719  /*--- Local variables for reading the SU2 file. ---*/
720  string text_line;
721  ifstream mesh_file;
722 
723  /*--- Open grid file ---*/
724  mesh_file.open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), ios::in);
725  if (mesh_file.fail()) {
726  SU2_MPI::Error(string("The SU2 mesh file named ") + val_mesh_filename + string(" was not found."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
727  }
728 
729  /*--- Read the SU2 mesh file until the dimension data is reached
730  or when it can be decided that it is not present. ---*/
731  while( getline (mesh_file, text_line) ) {
732 
733  /*--- Search for the "NDIME" keyword to determine the number
734  of dimensions. ---*/
735  if(text_line.find ("NDIME=",0) != string::npos) {
736  text_line.erase (0,6); nDim = atoi(text_line.c_str());
737  break;
738  }
739 
740  /*--- If one of the keywords NELEM or NPOIN, NMARK is encountered,
741  it can be assumed that the NZONE keyword is not present and
742  the loop can be terminated. ---*/
743  if(text_line.find ("NELEM=",0) != string::npos) break;
744  if(text_line.find ("NPOIN=",0) != string::npos) break;
745  if(text_line.find ("NMARK=",0) != string::npos) break;
746  }
747 
748  mesh_file.close();
749 
750  /*--- Throw an error if the dimension was not found. ---*/
751  if (nDim == -1) {
752  SU2_MPI::Error(val_mesh_filename + string(" is not an SU2 mesh file or has the wrong format \n ('NDIME=' not found). Please check."),
753  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
754  }
755 
756  break;
757  }
758 
759  case CGNS_GRID: {
760 
761 #ifdef HAVE_CGNS
762 
763  /*--- Local variables which are needed when calling the CGNS mid-level API. ---*/
764  int fn, nbases, file_type;
765  int cell_dim, phys_dim;
766  char basename[CGNS_STRING_SIZE];
767 
768  /*--- Check whether the supplied file is truly a CGNS file. ---*/
769  if ( cg_is_cgns(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), &file_type) != CG_OK ) {
770  SU2_MPI::Error(val_mesh_filename +
771  string(" was not found or is not a properly formatted CGNS file.\n") +
772  string("Note that SU2 expects unstructured CGNS files in ADF data format."),
773  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
774  }
775 
776  /*--- Open the CGNS file for reading. The value of fn returned
777  is the specific index number for this file and will be
778  repeatedly used in the function calls. ---*/
779  if (cg_open(val_mesh_filename.c_str(), CG_MODE_READ, &fn) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
780 
781  /*--- Get the number of databases. This is the highest node
782  in the CGNS heirarchy. ---*/
783  if (cg_nbases(fn, &nbases) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
784 
785  /*--- Check if there is more than one database. Throw an
786  error if there is because this reader can currently
787  only handle one database. ---*/
788  if ( nbases > 1 )
789  SU2_MPI::Error("CGNS reader currently incapable of handling more than 1 database." ,
790  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
791 
792  /*--- Read the database. Note that the indexing starts at 1.
793  Afterwards close the file again. ---*/
794  if (cg_base_read(fn, 1, basename, &cell_dim, &phys_dim) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
795  if (cg_close(fn) != CG_OK) cg_error_exit();
796 
797  /*--- Set the problem dimension as read from the CGNS file ---*/
798  nDim = cell_dim;
799 
800 #else
801  SU2_MPI::Error(string(" SU2 built without CGNS support. \n") +
802  string(" To use CGNS, build SU2 accordingly."),
803  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
804 #endif
805 
806  break;
807  }
808  case RECTANGLE: {
809  nDim = 2;
810  break;
811  }
812  case BOX: {
813  nDim = 3;
814  break;
815  }
816  }
817 
818  /*--- After reading the mesh, assert that the dimension is equal to 2 or 3. ---*/
819  assert((nDim == 2) || (nDim == 3));
820 
821  return (unsigned short) nDim;
822 }

1088 
1089 void CConfig::SetConfig_Options() {
1090 
1091  // This config file is parsed by a number of programs to make it easy to write SU2
1092  // wrapper scripts (in python, go, etc.) so please do
1093  // the best you can to follow the established format. It's very hard to parse c++ code
1094  // and none of us that write the parsers want to write a full c++ interpreter. Please
1095  // play nice with the existing format so that you don't break the existing scripts.
1096 
1097  /* BEGIN_CONFIG_OPTIONS */
1098 
1099  /*!\par CONFIG_CATEGORY: Problem Definition \ingroup Config */
1100  /*--- Options related to problem definition and partitioning ---*/
1101 
1102  /*!\brief SOLVER \n DESCRIPTION: Type of solver \n Options: see \link Solver_Map \endlink \n DEFAULT: NONE \ingroup Config*/

2977 void CConfig::SetConfig_Parsing(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE]) {
2978 
2979  ifstream case_file;
2980 
2981  /*--- Read the configuration file ---*/
2982 
2983  case_file.open(case_filename, ios::in);
2984 
2985  if (case_file.fail()) {
2986  SU2_MPI::Error("The configuration file (.cfg) is missing!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
2987  }
2988 
2989  SetConfig_Parsing(case_file);
2990 
2991  case_file.close();
2992 
2993 }
2994 
2995 void CConfig::SetConfig_Parsing(istream& config_buffer){
2996 
2997  string text_line, option_name;
2998  vector<string> option_value;
2999 
3000  string errorString;
3001 
3002  const int max_err_count = 30; // Maximum number of errors to print before stopping
3003  int err_count = 0; // How many errors have we found in the config file
3004  int line_count = 1;
3005 
3006  map<string, bool> included_options;
3007 
3008  /*--- Parse the configuration file and set the options ---*/
3009 
3010  while (getline (config_buffer, text_line)) {
3011 
3012  if (err_count >= max_err_count) {
3013  errorString.append("Too many errors, stopping parse.");
3014  break;
3015  }
3016 
3017  PrintingToolbox::trim(text_line);
3018 
3019  /*--- Check if there is a line continuation character at the
3020  * end of the current line or somewhere in between (the rest is ignored then).
3021  * If yes, read until there is a line without one or an empty line.
3022  * If there is a statement after a cont. char
3023  * throw an error. ---*/
3024 
3025  if (!text_line.empty() && (text_line.front() != '%')){
3026  while (text_line.back() == '\\' ||
3027  (PrintingToolbox::split(text_line, '\\').size() > 1)){
3028  string tmp;
3029  getline (config_buffer, tmp);
3030  line_count++;
3031  if (tmp.find_first_of('=') != string::npos){
3032  errorString.append("Line " + to_string(line_count) + ": Statement found after continuation character.\n");
3033  }
3034  PrintingToolbox::trim(tmp);
3035  if (tmp.front() != '%'){
3036  text_line = PrintingToolbox::split(text_line, '\\')[0];
3037  text_line += " " + tmp;
3038  }
3039  }
3040  }
3041 
3042  if (TokenizeString(text_line, option_name, option_value)) {
3043  /*--- See if it's a python option ---*/
3044 
3045  if (option_map.find(option_name) == option_map.end()) {
3046  string newString;
3047  newString.append("Line " + to_string(line_count) + " " + option_name);
3048  newString.append(": invalid option name");
3049  newString.append(". Check current SU2 options in config_template.cfg.");
3050  newString.append("\n");
3051  if (!option_name.compare("SINGLEZONE_DRIVER"))
3052  newString.append("Option SINGLEZONE_DRIVER is deprecated, it does not have a replacement.\n\n");
3053  else if (!option_name.compare("DYN_TIMESTEP"))
3054  newString.append("DYN_TIMESTEP is deprecated. Use TIME_STEP instead.\n\n");
3055  else if (!option_name.compare("DYN_TIME"))
3056  newString.append("DYN_TIME is deprecated. Use MAX_TIME instead.\n\n");
3057  else if (!option_name.compare("DYNAMIC_ANALYSIS"))
3058  newString.append("DYNAMIC_ANALYSIS is deprecated. Use TIME_DOMAIN instead.\n\n");
3059  else if (!option_name.compare("SPECIES_USE_STRONG_BC"))
3060  newString.append("SPECIES_USE_STRONG_BC is deprecated. Use MARKER_SPECIES_STRONG_BC= (marker1, ...) instead.\n\n");
3061  else {
3062  /*--- Find the most likely candidate for the unrecognized option, based on the length
3063  of start and end character sequences shared by candidates and the option. ---*/
3064  auto countMatchChars = [&option_name](const string& candidate) {
3065  const size_t sz1 = option_name.size(), sz2 = candidate.size();
3066  size_t nMatch = 0;
3067  for (size_t i=0; i<min(sz1,sz2); ++i) {
3068  if (option_name[i] == candidate[i]) nMatch++;
3069  else break;
3070  }
3071  for (size_t i=0; i<min(sz1,sz2); ++i) {
3072  if (option_name[sz1-1-i] == candidate[sz2-1-i]) nMatch++;
3073  else break;
3074  }
3075  return nMatch;
3076  };
3077  string match;
3078  size_t maxScore = 0;
3079  for (auto& candidate : option_map) {
3080  auto score = countMatchChars(candidate.first);
3081  if (score > maxScore) {
3082  maxScore = score;
3083  match = candidate.first;
3084  }
3085  }
3086  newString.append("Did you mean ");
3087  newString.append(match);
3088  newString.append("?\n");
3089  }
3090  errorString.append(newString);
3091  err_count++;
3092  line_count++;
3093  continue;
3094  }
3095 
3096  /*--- Option exists, check if the option has already been in the config file ---*/
3097 
3098  if (included_options.find(option_name) != included_options.end()) {
3099  string newString;
3100  newString.append("Line " + to_string(line_count) + " " + option_name);
3101  newString.append(": option appears twice");
3102  newString.append("\n");
3103  errorString.append(newString);
3104  err_count++;
3105  line_count++;
3106  continue;
3107  }
3108 
3109  /*--- New found option. Add it to the map, and delete from all options ---*/
3110 
3111  included_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(option_name, true));
3112  all_options.erase(option_name);
3113 
3114  /*--- Set the value and check error ---*/
3115 
3116  string out = option_map[option_name]->SetValue(option_value);
3117  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
3118  /*--- valid option, but deprecated value ---*/
3119  if (!option_name.compare("KIND_TURB_MODEL")) {
3120  if (option_value[0] == "SST_SUST")
3121  errorString.append("Option KIND_TURB_MODEL=SST_SUST is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SST, SST_OPTIONS=SUSTAINING instead.\n");
3122  else if (option_value[0] == "SA_NEG")
3123  errorString.append("Option KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA_NEG is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA, SA_OPTIONS=NEGATIVE instead.\n");
3124  else if (option_value[0] == "SA_E")
3125  errorString.append("Option KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA_E is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA, SA_OPTIONS=EDWARDS instead.\n");
3126  else if (option_value[0] == "SA_COMP")
3127  errorString.append("Option KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA_COMP is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA, SA_OPTIONS=COMPRESSIBILITY instead.\n");
3128  else if (option_value[0] == "SA_E_COMP")
3129  errorString.append("Option KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA_E_COMP is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA, SA_OPTIONS=EDWARDS,COMPRESSIBILITY instead.\n");
3130  } else if (!option_name.compare("KIND_TRANS_MODEL")) {
3131  if (option_value[0] == "BC")
3132  errorString.append("Option KIND_TRANS_MODEL=BC is deprecated. Use KIND_TURB_MODEL=SA, SA_OPTIONS=BCM instead.\n");
3133  }
3134  errorString.append(out);
3135  errorString.append("\n");
3136  err_count++;
3137  }
3138  }
3139  line_count++;
3140  }
3141 
3142  /*--- See if there were any errors parsing the config file ---*/
3143 
3144  if (!errorString.empty()) {
3145  SU2_MPI::Error(errorString, CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3146  }
3147 }

3149 void CConfig::SetDefaultFromConfig(CConfig *config){
3150 
3151  map<string, bool> noInheritance = {{"SCREEN_OUTPUT", true},{"HISTORY_OUTPUT", true}};
3152 
3153  map<string, bool>::iterator iter = all_options.begin(), curr_iter;
3154 
3155  while (iter != all_options.end()){
3156  curr_iter = iter++;
3157  if (!config->option_map[curr_iter->first]->GetValue().empty() && !noInheritance[curr_iter->first]){
3158  option_map[curr_iter->first]->SetValue(config->option_map[curr_iter->first]->GetValue());
3159  all_options.erase(curr_iter);
3160  }
3161  }

3174 bool CConfig::SetRunTime_Parsing(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE]) {
3175  string text_line, option_name;
3176  ifstream case_file;
3177  vector<string> option_value;
3178 
3179  /*--- Read the configuration file ---*/
3180 
3181  case_file.open(case_filename, ios::in);
3182 
3183  if (case_file.fail()) { return false; }
3184 
3185  string errorString;
3186 
3187  int err_count = 0; // How many errors have we found in the config file
3188  const int max_err_count = 30; // Maximum number of errors to print before stopping
3189 
3190  map<string, bool> included_options;
3191 
3192  /*--- Parse the configuration file and set the options ---*/
3193 
3194  while (getline (case_file, text_line)) {
3195 
3196  if (err_count >= max_err_count) {
3197  errorString.append("Too many errors, stopping parse.");
3198  break;
3199  }
3200 
3201  if (TokenizeString(text_line, option_name, option_value)) {
3202 
3203  if (option_map.find(option_name) == option_map.end()) {
3204 
3205  /*--- See if it's a python option ---*/
3206 
3207  string newString;
3208  newString.append(option_name);
3209  newString.append(": invalid option name");
3210  newString.append("\n");
3211  errorString.append(newString);
3212  err_count++;
3213  continue;
3214  }
3215 
3216  /*--- Option exists, check if the option has already been in the config file ---*/
3217 
3218  if (included_options.find(option_name) != included_options.end()) {
3219  string newString;
3220  newString.append(option_name);
3221  newString.append(": option appears twice");
3222  newString.append("\n");
3223  errorString.append(newString);
3224  err_count++;
3225  continue;
3226  }
3227 
3228  /*--- New found option. Add it to the map, and delete from all options ---*/
3229 
3230  included_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(option_name, true));
3231  all_options.erase(option_name);
3232 
3233  /*--- Set the value and check error ---*/
3234 
3235  string out = option_map[option_name]->SetValue(option_value);
3236  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
3237  errorString.append(out);
3238  errorString.append("\n");
3239  err_count++;
3240  }
3241 
3242  }
3243  }
3244 
3245  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
3246 
3247  for (auto iter = all_options.begin(); iter != all_options.end(); ++iter) {
3248  option_map[iter->first]->SetDefault();
3249  }
3250 
3251  /*--- See if there were any errors parsing the runtime file ---*/
3252 
3253  if (!errorString.empty()) {
3254  SU2_MPI::Error(errorString, CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3255  }
3256 
3257  case_file.close();
3258 
3259  return true;
3260 
3261 }

3304 void CConfig::SetnZone(){
3305 
3306  /*--- Just as a clarification --- */
3307 
3308  if (Multizone_Problem == NO && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::MULTIPHYSICS){
3309  nZone = 1;
3310  }
3311 
3312  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::MULTIPHYSICS){
3313  Multizone_Problem = YES;
3314  if (nConfig_Files == 0){
3315  SU2_MPI::Error("CONFIG_LIST must be provided if PHYSICAL_PROBLEM=MULTIPHYSICS", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3316  }
3317  }
3318 
3319  if (Multizone_Problem == YES){
3320 
3321  /*--- Some basic multizone checks ---*/
3322 
3323  if (nMarker_ZoneInterface % 2 != 0){
3324  SU2_MPI::Error("Number of markers in MARKER_ZONE_INTERFACE must be a multiple of 2", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3325  }
3326 
3327  if (Multizone_Mesh){
3328 
3329  /*--- Get the number of zones from the mesh file --- */
3330 
3331  nZone = GetnZone(Mesh_FileName, Mesh_FileFormat);
3332 
3333  /*--- If config list is set, make sure number matches number of zones in mesh file --- */
3334 
3335  if (nConfig_Files != 0 && (nZone != nConfig_Files)){
3336  SU2_MPI::Error("Number of CONFIG_LIST must match number of zones in mesh file.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3337  }
3338  } else {
3339 
3340  /*--- Number of zones is determined from the number of config files provided --- */
3341 
3342  if (nConfig_Files == 0){
3343  SU2_MPI::Error("If MULTIZONE_MESH is set to YES, you must provide a list of config files using CONFIG_LIST option", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3344  }
3345  nZone = nConfig_Files;
3346 
3347  }
3348 
3349  /*--- Check if subconfig files exist --- */
3350 
3351  if (nConfig_Files != 0){
3352  for (unsigned short iConfig = 0; iConfig < nConfig_Files; iConfig++){
3353  ifstream f(Config_Filenames[iConfig].c_str());
3354  if (!f.good()){
3355  SU2_MPI::Error("Config file " + Config_Filenames[iConfig] + " defined in CONFIG_FILES does not exist", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3356  }
3357  }
3358  }
3359 
3360  }

3364 void CConfig::SetPostprocessing(SU2_COMPONENT val_software, unsigned short val_izone, unsigned short val_nDim) {
3365 
3366  unsigned short iCFL, iMarker;
3367  bool ideal_gas = ((Kind_FluidModel == STANDARD_AIR) ||
3368  (Kind_FluidModel == IDEAL_GAS) ||
3369  (Kind_FluidModel == INC_IDEAL_GAS) ||
3370  (Kind_FluidModel == FLUID_MIXTURE) ||
3371  (Kind_FluidModel == FLUID_FLAMELET) ||
3372  (Kind_FluidModel == INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY) ||
3373  (Kind_FluidModel == CONSTANT_DENSITY));
3374  bool noneq_gas = ((Kind_FluidModel == MUTATIONPP) ||
3375  (Kind_FluidModel == SU2_NONEQ));
3376  bool standard_air = ((Kind_FluidModel == STANDARD_AIR));
3377  bool nemo = GetNEMOProblem();
3378 
3379  if (nZone > 1){
3380  Multizone_Problem = YES;
3381  }
3382 
3383  /*--- Set the default output files ---*/
3384  if (!OptionIsSet("OUTPUT_FILES")){
3385  nVolumeOutputFiles = 3;
3386  VolumeOutputFiles = new OUTPUT_TYPE[nVolumeOutputFiles];
3387  VolumeOutputFiles[0] = OUTPUT_TYPE::RESTART_BINARY;
3388  VolumeOutputFiles[1] = OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_XML;
3389  VolumeOutputFiles[2] = OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_PARAVIEW_XML;
3390  }
3391 
3392  /*--- Set the default output frequencies ---*/
3393  if (!OptionIsSet("OUTPUT_WRT_FREQ")){
3394  nVolumeOutputFrequencies = nVolumeOutputFiles;
3395  VolumeOutputFrequencies = new unsigned long [nVolumeOutputFrequencies];
3396 
3397  /*--- Using default frequency of 250 for all files when steady, and 1 for unsteady. ---*/
3398  for (auto iVolumeFreq = 0; iVolumeFreq < nVolumeOutputFrequencies; iVolumeFreq++){
3399  VolumeOutputFrequencies[iVolumeFreq] = Time_Domain ? 1 : 250;
3400  }
3401  } else if (nVolumeOutputFrequencies < nVolumeOutputFiles) {
3402  /*--- If there are fewer frequencies than files, repeat the last frequency.
3403  * This is useful to define 1 frequency for the restart file and 1 frequency for all the visualization files. ---*/
3404  auto* newFrequencies = new unsigned long[nVolumeOutputFiles];
3405  for (unsigned short i = 0; i < nVolumeOutputFrequencies; ++i) {
3406  newFrequencies[i] = VolumeOutputFrequencies[i];
3407  }
3408  for (auto i = nVolumeOutputFrequencies; i < nVolumeOutputFiles; ++i) {
3409  newFrequencies[i] = newFrequencies[i-1];
3410  }
3411  delete [] VolumeOutputFrequencies;
3412  VolumeOutputFrequencies = newFrequencies;
3413  nVolumeOutputFrequencies = nVolumeOutputFiles;
3414  }
3415 
3416  /*--- Check if SU2 was build with TecIO support, as that is required for Tecplot Binary output. ---*/
3417 #ifndef HAVE_TECIO
3418  for (unsigned short iVolumeFile = 0; iVolumeFile < nVolumeOutputFiles; iVolumeFile++){
3419  if (VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::TECPLOT_BINARY ||
3420  VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_TECPLOT_BINARY) {
3421  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Tecplot binary file requested in option OUTPUT_FILES but SU2 was built without TecIO support.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3422  }
3423  }
3424 #endif
3425 
3426  /*--- Check if SU2 was build with CGNS support, as that is required for CGNS output. ---*/
3427 #ifndef HAVE_CGNS
3428  for (unsigned short iVolumeFile = 0; iVolumeFile < nVolumeOutputFiles; iVolumeFile++) {
3429  if (VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::CGNS ||
3430  VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::SURFACE_CGNS) {
3431  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CGNS file requested in option OUTPUT_FILES but SU2 was built without CGNS support.\n"),CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3432  }
3433  }
3434 #endif
3435 
3436  /*--- Check if CoolProp is used with non-dimensionalization. ---*/
3437  if (Kind_FluidModel == COOLPROP && Ref_NonDim != DIMENSIONAL) {
3438  SU2_MPI::Error("CoolProp can not be used with non-dimensionalization.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3439  }
3440 
3441  /*--- STL_BINARY output not implemented yet, but already a value in option_structure.hpp---*/
3442  for (unsigned short iVolumeFile = 0; iVolumeFile < nVolumeOutputFiles; iVolumeFile++) {
3443  if (VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::STL_BINARY){
3444  SU2_MPI::Error(string("OUTPUT_FILES: 'STL_BINARY' output not implemented. Use 'STL' for ASCII output.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3445  }
3446  if (val_nDim == 2 && (VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::STL_ASCII || VolumeOutputFiles[iVolumeFile] == OUTPUT_TYPE::STL_BINARY)) {
3447  SU2_MPI::Error(string("OUTPUT_FILES: 'STL(_BINARY)' output only reasonable for 3D cases.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3448  }
3449  }
3450 
3451  /*--- Check if MESH_QUALITY is requested in VOLUME_OUTPUT and set the config boolean accordingly. ---*/
3452  Wrt_MeshQuality = false;
3453  for (unsigned short iField = 0; iField < nVolumeOutput; iField++) {
3454  if(VolumeOutput[iField].find("MESH_QUALITY") != string::npos) {
3455  Wrt_MeshQuality = true;
3456  }
3457  }
3458 
3459  /*--- Check if MULTIGRID is requested in VOLUME_OUTPUT and set the config boolean accordingly. ---*/
3460  Wrt_MultiGrid = false;
3461  for (unsigned short iField = 0; iField < nVolumeOutput; iField++) {
3462  if(VolumeOutput[iField].find("MULTIGRID") != string::npos) {
3463  Wrt_MultiGrid = true;
3464  }
3465  }
3466 
3467  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES && Kind_Turb_Model != TURB_MODEL::NONE){
3468  SU2_MPI::Error("KIND_TURB_MODEL must be NONE if SOLVER= NAVIER_STOKES", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3469  }
3470  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES && Kind_Turb_Model != TURB_MODEL::NONE){
3471  SU2_MPI::Error("KIND_TURB_MODEL must be NONE if SOLVER= INC_NAVIER_STOKES", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3472  }
3473  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::RANS && Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::NONE){
3474  SU2_MPI::Error("A turbulence model must be specified with KIND_TURB_MODEL if SOLVER= RANS", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3475  }
3476  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS && Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::NONE){
3477  SU2_MPI::Error("A turbulence model must be specified with KIND_TURB_MODEL if SOLVER= INC_RANS", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3478  }
3479 
3480  /*--- Postprocess SST_OPTIONS into structure. ---*/
3481  if (Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SST) {
3482  sstParsedOptions = ParseSSTOptions(SST_Options, nSST_Options, rank);
3483  } else if (Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SA) {
3484  saParsedOptions = ParseSAOptions(SA_Options, nSA_Options, rank);
3485  }
3486 
3487  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS && sstParsedOptions.compSarkar){
3488  SU2_MPI::Error("COMPRESSIBILITY-SARKAR only supported for SOLVER= RANS", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3489  }
3490 
3491  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS && sstParsedOptions.compWilcox){
3492  SU2_MPI::Error("COMPRESSIBILITY-WILCOX only supported for SOLVER= RANS", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3493  }
3494 
3495  /*--- Postprocess LM_OPTIONS into structure. ---*/
3496  if (Kind_Trans_Model == TURB_TRANS_MODEL::LM) {
3497  lmParsedOptions = ParseLMOptions(LM_Options, nLM_Options, rank, Kind_Turb_Model);
3498 
3499  /*--- Check if problem is 2D and LM2015 has been selected ---*/
3500  if (lmParsedOptions.LM2015 && val_nDim == 2) {
3501  SU2_MPI::Error("LM2015 is available only for 3D problems", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3502  }
3503  }
3504 
3505  /*--- Set the boolean Wall_Functions equal to true if there is a
3506  definition for the wall founctions ---*/
3507 
3508  Wall_Functions = false;
3509  if (nMarker_WallFunctions > 0) {
3510  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_WallFunctions; iMarker++) {
3511  if (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] != WALL_FUNCTIONS::NONE)
3512  Wall_Functions = true;
3513 
3514  if ((Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == WALL_FUNCTIONS::ADAPTIVE_FUNCTION) ||
3515  (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == WALL_FUNCTIONS::SCALABLE_FUNCTION) ||
3516  (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == WALL_FUNCTIONS::NONEQUILIBRIUM_MODEL))
3517  SU2_MPI::Error(string("For RANS problems, use NONE, STANDARD_WALL_FUNCTION or EQUILIBRIUM_WALL_MODEL.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3518 
3519  if (Kind_WallFunctions[iMarker] == WALL_FUNCTIONS::STANDARD_FUNCTION) {
3520  if ((Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::RANS) && (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS))
3521  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Wall model STANDARD_FUNCTION only available for RANS or INC_RANS.\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3522  if (nRough_Wall != 0)
3523  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Wall model STANDARD_FUNCTION and WALL_ROUGHNESS migh not be compatible. Checking required!\n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3524  }
3525 
3526  }
3527  }
3528 
3529  /*--- Initialize the AoA and Sideslip variables for the incompressible
3530  solver. This is typically unused (often internal flows). Also fixed CL
3531  mode for incompressible flows is not implemented ---*/
3532 
3533  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER ||
3534  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES ||
3535  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) {
3536 
3537  /*--- Compute x-velocity with a safegaurd for 0.0. ---*/
3538 
3539  su2double Vx = 1e-10;
3540  if (vel_init[0] != 0.0) {
3541  Vx = vel_init[0];
3542  }
3543 
3544  /*--- Compute the angle-of-attack and sideslip. ---*/
3545 
3546  su2double alpha = 0.0, beta = 0.0;
3547  if (val_nDim == 2) {
3548  alpha = atan(vel_init[1]/Vx)*180.0/PI_NUMBER;
3549  } else {
3550  alpha = atan(vel_init[2]/Vx)*180.0/PI_NUMBER;
3551  beta = atan(vel_init[1]/Vx)*180.0/PI_NUMBER;
3552  }
3553 
3554  /*--- Set alpha and beta in the config class. ---*/
3555 
3556  SetAoA(alpha);
3557  SetAoS(beta);
3558 
3559  if (Fixed_CL_Mode) {
3560  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Fixed CL mode not implemented for the incompressible solver. \n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3561  }
3562 
3563  /*--- Inc CHT simulation, but energy equation of fluid is inactive. ---*/
3564  if (Multizone_Problem && (nMarker_CHTInterface > 0) && !Energy_Equation)
3565  SU2_MPI::Error(string("You probably want to set INC_ENERGY_EQUATION= YES for the fluid solver. \n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3566  }
3567 
3568  /*--- Check correctness and consistency of contact resistance options. ---*/
3569  if (nMarker_ContactResistance > 0) {
3570 
3571  /*--- Set constant contact resistance across CHT interfaces if a single value is provided. ---*/
3572  if (nMarker_ContactResistance == 1) {
3573  auto val_CHTInterface = CHT_ContactResistance[0];
3574  delete [] CHT_ContactResistance;
3575  CHT_ContactResistance = new su2double[nMarker_CHTInterface];
3576  for (auto iCHTMarker=0u; iCHTMarker < nMarker_CHTInterface; iCHTMarker++)
3577  CHT_ContactResistance[iCHTMarker] = val_CHTInterface;
3578  }else if((nMarker_CHTInterface/2) != nMarker_ContactResistance){
3579  SU2_MPI::Error("Number of CHT interfaces does not match number of contact resistances.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3580  }
3581  for (auto iCHTMarker=0u; iCHTMarker < nMarker_ContactResistance; iCHTMarker++){
3582  if (CHT_ContactResistance[iCHTMarker] < 0)
3583  SU2_MPI::Error("Contact resistance value should be positive.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3584  }
3585  }
3586 
3587  /*--- By default, in 2D we should use TWOD_AIRFOIL (independenly from the input file) ---*/
3588 
3589  if (val_nDim == 2) Geo_Description = TWOD_AIRFOIL;
3590 
3591  /*--- Store the SU2 module that we are executing. ---*/
3592 
3593  Kind_SU2 = val_software;
3594 
3595  /*--- Set limiter for no MUSCL reconstructions ---*/
3596 
3597  auto SetScalarDefaults = [](bool muscl, unsigned short& KindConvScheme, UPWIND& KindUpwind, LIMITER& KindLimiter) {
3598  if (KindConvScheme == NO_CONVECTIVE) {
3599  KindConvScheme = SPACE_UPWIND;
3600  KindUpwind = UPWIND::SCALAR_UPWIND;
3601  } else if (KindConvScheme == SPACE_CENTERED) {
3602  SU2_MPI::Error("Centered schemes are not available for scalar transport", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3603  }
3604  if (!muscl) KindLimiter = LIMITER::NONE;
3605  };
3606  SetScalarDefaults(MUSCL_Turb, Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb);
3607  SetScalarDefaults(MUSCL_Heat, Kind_ConvNumScheme_Heat, Kind_Upwind_Heat, Kind_SlopeLimit_Heat);
3608  SetScalarDefaults(MUSCL_Species, Kind_ConvNumScheme_Species, Kind_Upwind_Species, Kind_SlopeLimit_Species);
3609 
3610  if (MUSCL_Flow && (Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow == SPACE_CENTERED)) {
3611  if (OptionIsSet("MUSCL_FLOW")) {
3612  SU2_MPI::Error("Centered schemes do not use MUSCL reconstruction (use MUSCL_FLOW= NO).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3613  } else {
3614  MUSCL_Flow = false;
3615  }
3616  }
3617  if (MUSCL_AdjFlow && (Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow == SPACE_CENTERED)) {
3618  if (OptionIsSet("MUSCL_ADJFLOW")) {
3619  SU2_MPI::Error("Centered schemes do not use MUSCL reconstruction (use MUSCL_ADJFLOW= NO).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3620  } else {
3621  MUSCL_AdjFlow = false;
3622  }
3623  }
3624 
3625  if (!MUSCL_Flow || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow = LIMITER::NONE;
3626  if (!MUSCL_AdjFlow || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow = LIMITER::NONE;
3627  if (!MUSCL_AdjTurb || (Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjTurb == SPACE_CENTERED)) Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjTurb = LIMITER::NONE;
3628 
3629  /*--- Set the default for thrust in ActDisk ---*/
3630 
3631  if ((Kind_ActDisk == NET_THRUST) || (Kind_ActDisk == BC_THRUST)
3632  || (Kind_ActDisk == DRAG_MINUS_THRUST) || (Kind_ActDisk == MASSFLOW)
3633  || (Kind_ActDisk == POWER))
3634  ActDisk_Jump = RATIO;
3635 
3636  if(Marker_ActDiskBemInlet_CG && Marker_ActDiskBemInlet_Axis){
3637  if(nMarker_ActDiskBemInlet_CG != nMarker_ActDiskBemInlet_Axis){
3638  SU2_MPI::Error("Marker lists supplied to MARKER_ACTDISK_BEM_CG and MARKER_ACTDISK_BEM_AXIS must be identical.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3639  }
3640  for(iMarker=0; iMarker<nMarker_ActDiskBemInlet_CG; iMarker++){
3641  if(Marker_ActDiskBemInlet_CG[iMarker]!=Marker_ActDiskBemInlet_Axis[iMarker]){
3642  SU2_MPI::Error("Marker lists supplied to MARKER_ACTDISK_BEM_CG and MARKER_ACTDISK_BEM_AXIS must be identical.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3643  }
3644  }
3645  }
3646 
3647  if(Marker_ActDiskBemOutlet_CG && Marker_ActDiskBemOutlet_Axis){
3648  if(nMarker_ActDiskBemOutlet_CG != nMarker_ActDiskBemOutlet_Axis){
3649  SU2_MPI::Error("Marker lists supplied to MARKER_ACTDISK_BEM_CG and MARKER_ACTDISK_BEM_AXIS must be identical.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3650  }
3651  for(iMarker=0; iMarker<nMarker_ActDiskBemOutlet_CG; iMarker++){
3652  if(Marker_ActDiskBemOutlet_CG[iMarker]!=Marker_ActDiskBemOutlet_Axis[iMarker]){
3653  SU2_MPI::Error("Marker lists supplied to MARKER_ACTDISK_BEM_CG and MARKER_ACTDISK_BEM_AXIS must be identical.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3654  }
3655  }
3656  }
3657 
3658  /*--- Error-catching and automatic array adjustments for objective, marker, and weights arrays --- */
3659 
3660  /*--- If Kind_Obj has not been specified, these arrays need to take a default --*/
3661 
3662  if (Weight_ObjFunc == nullptr && Kind_ObjFunc == nullptr) {
3663  Kind_ObjFunc = new unsigned short[1];
3664  Kind_ObjFunc[0] = DRAG_COEFFICIENT;
3665  Weight_ObjFunc = new su2double[1];
3666  Weight_ObjFunc[0] = 1.0;
3667  nObj=1;
3668  nObjW=1;
3669  }
3670 
3671  /*--- Maker sure that arrays are the same length ---*/
3672 
3673  if (nObj>0) {
3674  if (nMarker_Monitoring!=nObj && Marker_Monitoring!= nullptr) {
3675  if (nMarker_Monitoring==1) {
3676  /*-- If only one marker was listed with multiple objectives, set that marker as the marker for each objective ---*/
3677  nMarker_Monitoring = nObj;
3678  string marker = Marker_Monitoring[0];
3679  delete[] Marker_Monitoring;
3680  Marker_Monitoring = new string[nMarker_Monitoring];
3681  for (iMarker=0; iMarker<nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++)
3682  Marker_Monitoring[iMarker] = marker;
3683  }
3684  else if(nObj==1){
3685  /*--- If one objective and more than one marker: repeat objective over each marker, evenly weighted ---*/
3686  unsigned int obj = Kind_ObjFunc[0];
3687  su2double wt=1.0;
3688  delete[] Kind_ObjFunc;
3689  if (Weight_ObjFunc!=nullptr){
3690  wt = Weight_ObjFunc[0];
3691  delete[] Weight_ObjFunc;
3692  }
3693  Kind_ObjFunc = new short unsigned int[nMarker_Monitoring];
3694  Weight_ObjFunc = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
3695  for (unsigned short iObj=0; iObj<nMarker_Monitoring; iObj++){
3696  Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] = obj;
3697  Weight_ObjFunc[iObj] = wt;
3698  }
3699  nObjW = nObj;
3700  }
3701  else if(nObj>1) {
3702  SU2_MPI::Error("When using more than one OBJECTIVE_FUNCTION, MARKER_MONITORING must be the same length or length 1.\n"
3703  "For multiple surfaces per objective, either use one objective or list the objective multiple times.\n"
3704  "For multiple objectives per marker either use one marker or list the marker multiple times.\n"
3705  "Similar rules apply for multi-objective optimization using OPT_OBJECTIVE rather than OBJECTIVE_FUNCTION.",
3706  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3707  }
3708  }
3709  }
3710 
3711  /*-- Correct for case where Weight_ObjFunc has not been provided or has length < kind_objfunc---*/
3712 
3713  if (nObjW<nObj) {
3714  if (Weight_ObjFunc!= nullptr && nObjW>1) {
3715  SU2_MPI::Error("The option OBJECTIVE_WEIGHT must either have the same length as OBJECTIVE_FUNCTION,\n"
3716  "be lenght 1, or be deleted from the config file (equal weights will be applied).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3717  }
3718  Weight_ObjFunc = new su2double[nObj];
3719  for (unsigned short iObj=0; iObj<nObj; iObj++)
3720  Weight_ObjFunc[iObj] = 1.0;
3721  }
3722 
3723  /*--- One final check for multi-objective with the set of objectives
3724  that are not counted per-surface. We will disable multi-objective here. ---*/
3725 
3726  if (nObj > 1) {
3727  unsigned short Obj_0 = Kind_ObjFunc[0];
3728  for (unsigned short iObj=1; iObj<nObj; iObj++){
3729  switch(Kind_ObjFunc[iObj]) {
3730  case INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE:
3731  case INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX:
3732  case THRUST_COEFFICIENT:
3733  case TORQUE_COEFFICIENT:
3734  case FIGURE_OF_MERIT:
3735  case SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE:
3736  case SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE:
3737  case SURFACE_STATIC_TEMPERATURE:
3738  case SURFACE_MASSFLOW:
3739  case SURFACE_UNIFORMITY:
3740  case SURFACE_SECONDARY:
3741  case SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION:
3742  case SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM:
3743  case SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP:
3744  case SURFACE_SPECIES_0:
3745  case SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE:
3746  case CUSTOM_OBJFUNC:
3747  if (Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] != Obj_0) {
3748  SU2_MPI::Error("The following objectives can only be used for the first surface in a multi-objective \n"
3749  "problem or as a single objective applied to multiple monitoring markers:\n"
3750  "INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE, INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX, THRUST_COEFFICIENT, TORQUE_COEFFICIENT\n"
3751  "FIGURE_OF_MERIT, SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE, SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE, SURFACE_MASSFLOW\n"
3752  "SURFACE_UNIFORMITY, SURFACE_SECONDARY, SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION, SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM\n"
3753  "SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP, SURFACE_STATIC_TEMPERATURE, SURFACE_SPECIES_0\n"
3754  "SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE, CUSTOM_OBJFUNC.\n", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3755  }
3756  break;
3757  default:
3758  break;
3759  }
3760  }
3761  }
3762 
3763  if (nObj > 0){
3764  if (Kind_ObjFunc[0] == CUSTOM_OBJFUNC && CustomObjFunc.empty() && !Multizone_Problem) {
3765  SU2_MPI::Error("The expression for the custom objective function was not set.\n"
3766  "For example, CUSTOM_OBJFUNC= LIFT/DRAG", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3767  }
3768  }
3769 
3770  /*--- Check for unsteady problem ---*/
3771 
3772  if ((TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::TIME_STEPPING ||
3773  TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_1ST ||
3774  TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::DT_STEPPING_2ND) && !Time_Domain){
3775  SU2_MPI::Error("TIME_DOMAIN must be set to YES if TIME_MARCHING is "
3776  "TIME_STEPPING, DUAL_TIME_STEPPING-1ST_ORDER or DUAL_TIME_STEPPING-2ND_ORDER", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3777  }
3778 
3779  if (Time_Domain){
3780  Delta_UnstTime = Time_Step;
3781 
3782  if (TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::TIME_STEPPING){ InnerIter = 1; }
3783 
3784  /*--- Set History write freq for inner and outer iteration to zero by default, so only time iterations write. ---*/
3785  if (!OptionIsSet("HISTORY_WRT_FREQ_INNER")) { HistoryWrtFreq[2] = 0; }
3786  if (!OptionIsSet("HISTORY_WRT_FREQ_OUTER")) { HistoryWrtFreq[1] = 0; }
3787 
3788  if (Restart == NO) {
3789  Restart_Iter = 0;
3790  } else {
3791  if(nTimeIter <= Restart_Iter) SU2_MPI::Error("TIME_ITER must be larger than RESTART_ITER.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3792  }
3793 
3794  /*--- WINDOW_START_ITER must be larger than or equal to: RESTART_ITER. Otherwise, the running average is wrong. ---*/
3795  if (OptionIsSet("WINDOW_START_ITER")) {
3796  if (StartWindowIteration < Restart_Iter) {
3797  SU2_MPI::Error("WINDOW_START_ITER must be larger than or equal to: RESTART_ITER!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3798  }
3799  } else {
3800  /*--- Enforced default behavior: start of the window is the first new iteration. ---*/
3801  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << "WARNING: Setting WINDOW_START_ITER = RESTART_ITER for meaningful running average.\n";
3802  StartWindowIteration = Restart_Iter;
3803  }
3804 
3805  if (Time_Step <= 0.0 && Unst_CFL == 0.0){ SU2_MPI::Error("Invalid value for TIME_STEP.", CURRENT_FUNCTION); }
3806  } else {
3807  nTimeIter = 1;
3808  Time_Step = 0;
3809 
3810  /*--- Entry 0 corresponds to unsteady simulation so for steady simulation are just set to 1. ---*/
3811  ScreenWrtFreq[0] = 1;
3812  HistoryWrtFreq[0] = 1;
3813 
3814  if (TimeMarching != TIME_MARCHING::HARMONIC_BALANCE) { TimeMarching = TIME_MARCHING::STEADY; }
3815  }
3816 
3817  if (Time_Domain && !GetWrt_Restart_Overwrite()){
3818  SU2_MPI::Error("Appending iterations to the filename (WRT_RESTART_OVERWRITE=NO) is incompatible with transient problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3819  }
3820  if (Time_Domain && !GetWrt_Surface_Overwrite()){
3821  SU2_MPI::Error("Appending iterations to the filename (WRT_SURFACE_OVERWRITE=NO) is incompatible with transient problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3822  }
3823  if (Time_Domain && !GetWrt_Volume_Overwrite()){
3824  SU2_MPI::Error("Appending iterations to the filename (WRT_VOLUME_OVERWRITE=NO) is incompatible with transient problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3825  }
3826 
3827 
3828  /*--- Ensure that Discard_InFiles is false, owerwise the gradient could be wrong ---*/
3829 
3830  if ((ContinuousAdjoint || DiscreteAdjoint) && Fixed_CL_Mode && !Eval_dOF_dCX)
3831  Discard_InFiles = false;
3832 
3833  /*--- Deactivate the multigrid in the adjoint problem ---*/
3834 
3835  if ((ContinuousAdjoint && !MG_AdjointFlow) ||
3836  (TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::TIME_STEPPING)) { nMGLevels = 0; }
3837 
3838  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::EULER ||
3839  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES ||
3840  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::RANS ||
3841  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER ||
3842  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES ||
3843  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER ||
3844  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES ||
3845  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS ||
3846  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_LES){
3847  Kind_Regime = ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE;
3848  } else if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER ||
3849  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES ||
3850  Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS){
3851  Kind_Regime = ENUM_REGIME::INCOMPRESSIBLE;
3852  } else {
3853  Kind_Regime = ENUM_REGIME::NO_FLOW;
3854  }
3855 
3856  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && ContinuousAdjoint && (Ref_NonDim == DIMENSIONAL) && (Kind_SU2 == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_CFD)) {
3857  cout << "WARNING: The adjoint solver should use a non-dimensional flow solution." << endl;
3858  }
3859 
3860  /*--- Initialize non-physical points/reconstructions to zero ---*/
3861 
3862  Nonphys_Points = 0;
3863  Nonphys_Reconstr = 0;
3864 
3865  /*--- Set the number of external iterations to 1 for the steady state problem ---*/
3866 
3867  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY) {
3868  nMGLevels = 0;
3869  if (Kind_Struct_Solver == STRUCT_DEFORMATION::SMALL){
3870  MinLogResidual = log10(Linear_Solver_Error);
3871  }
3872  }
3873 
3874  Radiation = (Kind_Radiation != RADIATION_MODEL::NONE);
3875 
3876  /*--- Check for unsupported features. ---*/
3877 
3878  if ((Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::EULER && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::RANS) && (TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::HARMONIC_BALANCE)){
3879  SU2_MPI::Error("Harmonic Balance not yet implemented for the incompressible solver.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3880  }
3881 
3882  /*--- Check for Fluid model consistency ---*/
3883 
3884  if (standard_air) {
3885  if (Gamma != 1.4 || Gas_Constant != 287.058) {
3886  Gamma = 1.4;
3887  Gas_Constant = 287.058;
3888  }
3889  }
3890 
3891 /*--- Set default values for various fluid properties. ---*/
3892 
3893  const su2double Molecular_Weight_Default = 28.96;
3894  const su2double Mu_Constant_Default = (SystemMeasurements == SI) ? 1.716E-5 : (1.716E-5 / 47.88025898);
3895  const su2double Mu_Ref_Default = Mu_Constant_Default;
3896  const su2double Mu_Temperature_Ref_Default = (SystemMeasurements == SI) ? 273.15 : (273.15 * 1.8);
3897  const su2double Mu_S_Default = (SystemMeasurements == SI) ? 110.4 : (110.4 * 1.8);
3898  const su2double Specific_Heat_Cp_Default = 1004.703;
3899  const su2double Thermal_Conductivity_Constant_Default = (SystemMeasurements == SI) ? 2.57E-2 : (2.57E-2 * 0.577789317);
3900  const su2double Prandtl_Lam_Default = 0.72;
3901  const su2double Prandtl_Turb_Default = 0.9;
3902  const su2double Lewis_Number_Default = 1.0;
3903 
3904  auto SetDefaultIfEmpty = [](su2double*& array, unsigned short& size, const su2double& default_val) {
3905  if (array == nullptr) {
3906  array = new su2double[1];
3907  array[0] = default_val;
3908  size = 1;
3909  }
3910  };
3911 
3912  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Molecular_Weight, nMolecular_Weight, Molecular_Weight_Default);
3913  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Specific_Heat_Cp, nSpecific_Heat_Cp, Specific_Heat_Cp_Default);
3914  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Mu_Constant, nMu_Constant, Mu_Constant_Default);
3915  if (Mu_Ref == nullptr && Mu_Temperature_Ref == nullptr && Mu_S == nullptr) {
3916  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Mu_Ref, nMu_Ref, Mu_Ref_Default);
3917  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Mu_Temperature_Ref, nMu_Temperature_Ref, Mu_Temperature_Ref_Default);
3918  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Mu_S, nMu_S, Mu_S_Default);
3919  }
3920  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Thermal_Conductivity_Constant, nThermal_Conductivity_Constant,
3921  Thermal_Conductivity_Constant_Default);
3922  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Prandtl_Lam, nPrandtl_Lam, Prandtl_Lam_Default);
3923  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Prandtl_Turb, nPrandtl_Turb, Prandtl_Turb_Default);
3924  SetDefaultIfEmpty(Constant_Lewis_Number, nConstant_Lewis_Number, Lewis_Number_Default);
3925 
3926  Variable_Density = ((Kind_DensityModel == INC_DENSITYMODEL::VARIABLE) || (Kind_DensityModel == INC_DENSITYMODEL::FLAMELET));
3927 
3928  /*--- Check whether inputs for FLUID_MIXTURE are correctly specified. ---*/
3929 
3930  if (Kind_FluidModel == FLUID_MIXTURE) {
3931  /*--- Check whether the number of entries of each specified fluid property equals the number of transported scalar
3932  equations solved + 1. nMolecular_Weight and nSpecific_Heat_Cp are used because it is required for the fluid mixing models.
3933  * Cp is required in case of MIXTURE_FLUID_MODEL because the energy equation needs to be active.--- */
3934  if (nMolecular_Weight != nSpecies_Init + 1 || nSpecific_Heat_Cp != nSpecies_Init + 1) {
3935  SU2_MPI::Error(
3936  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for MOLECULAR_WEIGHT and SPECIFIC_HEAT_CP,\n"
3937  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3938  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3939  }
3940  /*--- Check whether the density model used is correct, in the case of FLUID_MIXTURE the density model must be
3941  VARIABLE. Otherwise, if the density model is CONSTANT, the scalars will not have influence the mixture density
3942  and it will remain constant through the complete domain. --- */
3943  if (Kind_DensityModel != INC_DENSITYMODEL::VARIABLE) {
3944  SU2_MPI::Error("The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the INC_DENSITY_MODEL option to be VARIABLE",
3945  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3946  }
3947  /*--- Check whether the Kind scalar model used is correct, in the case of FLUID_MIXTURE the kind scalar model must
3948  be SPECIES_TRANSPORT. Otherwise, if the scalar model is NONE, the species transport equations will not be solved.
3949  --- */
3950  if (Kind_Species_Model != SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT) {
3951  SU2_MPI::Error("The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the KIND_SCALAR_MODEL option to be SPECIES_TRANSPORT",
3952  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3953  }
3954 
3955  switch (Kind_ViscosityModel) {
3956  case VISCOSITYMODEL::CONSTANT:
3957  if (nMu_Constant != nSpecies_Init + 1) {
3958  SU2_MPI::Error(
3959  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for MU_CONSTANT,\n"
3960  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3961  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3962  }
3963  break;
3964  case VISCOSITYMODEL::SUTHERLAND:
3965  if ((nMu_Ref != nSpecies_Init + 1) || (nMu_Temperature_Ref != nSpecies_Init + 1) ||
3966  (nMu_S != nSpecies_Init + 1)) {
3967  SU2_MPI::Error(
3968  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for MU_REF, MU_T_REF and "
3969  "SUTHERLAND_CONSTANT,\n"
3970  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3971  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3972  }
3973  break;
3974  default:
3975  if (nSpecies_Init + 1 != 1) SU2_MPI::Error("Fluid mixture: viscosity model not available.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3976  break;
3977  }
3978 
3979  switch (Kind_ConductivityModel) {
3980  case CONDUCTIVITYMODEL::CONSTANT:
3981  if ((Kind_ConductivityModel_Turb == CONDUCTIVITYMODEL_TURB::CONSTANT_PRANDTL) &&
3982  (Kind_Turb_Model != TURB_MODEL::NONE)) {
3983  if ((nThermal_Conductivity_Constant != nSpecies_Init + 1) || (nPrandtl_Turb != nSpecies_Init + 1)) {
3984  SU2_MPI::Error(
3985  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for THERMAL_CONDUCTIVITY_CONSTANT and "
3986  "PRANDTL_TURB,\n"
3987  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3988  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3989  }
3990  } else {
3991  if (nThermal_Conductivity_Constant != nSpecies_Init + 1) {
3992  SU2_MPI::Error(
3993  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for THERMAL_CONDUCTIVITY_CONSTANT,\n"
3994  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
3995  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
3996  }
3997  }
3998  break;
3999  case CONDUCTIVITYMODEL::CONSTANT_PRANDTL:
4000  if (Kind_ConductivityModel_Turb == CONDUCTIVITYMODEL_TURB::CONSTANT_PRANDTL) {
4001  if ((nPrandtl_Lam != nSpecies_Init + 1) || (nPrandtl_Turb != nSpecies_Init + 1)) {
4002  SU2_MPI::Error(
4003  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for PRANDTL_LAM and PRANDTL_TURB,\n"
4004  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
4005  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4006  }
4007  } else {
4008  if (nPrandtl_Lam != nSpecies_Init + 1) {
4009  SU2_MPI::Error(
4010  "The use of FLUID_MIXTURE requires the number of entries for PRANDTL_LAM,\n"
4011  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT + 1",
4012  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4013  }
4014  }
4015  break;
4016  default:
4017  if (nSpecies_Init + 1 != 1) SU2_MPI::Error("Conductivity model not available.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
4018  break;
4019  }

5000
