5002 
5003  /*--- If there are not design variables defined in the file ---*/
5004 
5005  if (nDV == 0) {
5006  nDV = 1;
5007  Design_Variable = new unsigned short [nDV];
5008  Design_Variable[0] = NO_DEFORMATION;
5009  }
5010 
5011  /*--- Checks for incompressible flow problems. ---*/
5012 
5013  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER) {
5014  /*--- Force inviscid problems to use constant density and disable energy. ---*/
5015  if (Kind_DensityModel != INC_DENSITYMODEL::CONSTANT || Energy_Equation) {
5016  SU2_MPI::Error("Inviscid incompressible problems must be constant density (no energy eqn.).\n Use DENSITY_MODEL= CONSTANT and ENERGY_EQUATION= NO.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5017  }
5018  }
5019 
5020  /*--- Default values should recover original incompressible behavior (for old config files). ---*/
5021 
5022  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) {
5023  if ((Kind_DensityModel == INC_DENSITYMODEL::CONSTANT) || (Kind_DensityModel == INC_DENSITYMODEL::BOUSSINESQ))
5024  Kind_FluidModel = CONSTANT_DENSITY;
5025  }
5026 
5027  if ((Kind_DensityModel != INC_DENSITYMODEL::CONSTANT) && (Kind_Species_Model==SPECIES_MODEL::NONE)) Energy_Equation = true;
5028  /*--- For the flamelet combustion model, energy equation is a passive field, we lookup T and write it to the field ---*/
5029  if (Kind_Species_Model == SPECIES_MODEL::FLAMELET ) Energy_Equation = false;
5030 
5031  if (Kind_DensityModel == INC_DENSITYMODEL::BOUSSINESQ) {
5032  Energy_Equation = true;
5033  if (Body_Force) {
5034  SU2_MPI::Error("Body force and Boussinesq source terms are not currently compatible.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5035  }
5036  }
5037 
5038  if (Kind_DensityModel == INC_DENSITYMODEL::VARIABLE) {
5039  if (Kind_FluidModel != INC_IDEAL_GAS && Kind_FluidModel != INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY && Kind_FluidModel != FLUID_MIXTURE && Kind_FluidModel != FLUID_FLAMELET) {
5040  SU2_MPI::Error("Variable density incompressible solver limited to ideal gases.\n Check the fluid model options (use INC_IDEAL_GAS, INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5041  }
5042  }
5043 
5044  if (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) {
5045  if ((Kind_FluidModel == CONSTANT_DENSITY) || (Kind_FluidModel == INC_IDEAL_GAS) || (Kind_FluidModel == INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY)) {
5046  SU2_MPI::Error("Fluid model not compatible with compressible flows.\n CONSTANT_DENSITY/INC_IDEAL_GAS/INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY are for incompressible only.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5047  }
5048  }
5049 
5050  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) {
5051  if (Kind_ViscosityModel == VISCOSITYMODEL::SUTHERLAND) {
5052  if ((Kind_FluidModel != INC_IDEAL_GAS) && (Kind_FluidModel != INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY) && (Kind_FluidModel != FLUID_MIXTURE)) {
5053  SU2_MPI::Error("Sutherland's law only valid for ideal gases in incompressible flows.\n Must use VISCOSITY_MODEL=CONSTANT_VISCOSITY and set viscosity with\n MU_CONSTANT, or use DENSITY_MODEL= VARIABLE with FLUID_MODEL= INC_IDEAL_GAS or INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY for VISCOSITY_MODEL=SUTHERLAND.\n NOTE: FREESTREAM_VISCOSITY is no longer used for incompressible flows!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5054  }
5055  }
5056  }
5057 
5058  /*--- Vorticity confinement feature currently not supported for incompressible or non-equilibrium model or axisymmetric flows. ---*/
5059 
5060  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER
5061  || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES
5062  || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS
5063  || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER
5064  || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES
5065  || Axisymmetric)
5066  && VorticityConfinement) {
5067  SU2_MPI::Error("Vorticity confinement feature currently not supported for incompressible or non-equilibrium model or axisymmetric flows.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5068  }
5069 
5070  /*--- Actuator disk BEM method for propellers feature currently not supported for incompressible or non-equilibrium model or axisymmetric flows. ---*/
5071 
5072  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER
5073  || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES
5074  || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS
5075  || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER
5076  || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES
5077  || Axisymmetric)
5078  && ActDisk_DoubleSurface) {
5079  SU2_MPI::Error("Actuator disk BEM method for propellers feature currently not supported for incompressible or non-equilibrium model or axisymmetric flows.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5080  }
5081 
5082  /*--- Check the coefficients for the polynomial models. ---*/
5083 
5084  if (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES && Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) {
5085  if ((Kind_ViscosityModel == VISCOSITYMODEL::POLYNOMIAL) || (Kind_ConductivityModel == CONDUCTIVITYMODEL::POLYNOMIAL) || (Kind_FluidModel == INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY)) {
5086  SU2_MPI::Error("POLYNOMIAL_VISCOSITY and POLYNOMIAL_CONDUCTIVITY are for incompressible only currently.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5087  }
5088  }
5089 
5090  /*--- Data-driven fluid model is currently only supported for compressible flow problems. ---*/
5091  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) && (Kind_FluidModel == DATADRIVEN_FLUID)) {
5092  SU2_MPI::Error("Data-driven fluid model can only be used for compressible flows.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5093  }
5094 
5095  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) && (Kind_FluidModel == INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY)) {
5096  su2double sum = 0.0;
5097  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < N_POLY_COEFFS; iVar++) {
5098  sum += GetCp_PolyCoeff(iVar);
5099  }
5100  if ((N_POLY_COEFFS < 1) || (sum == 0.0))
5101  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CP_POLYCOEFFS not set for fluid model INC_IDEAL_GAS_POLY. \n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5102  }
5103 
5104  if (((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS)) && (Kind_ViscosityModel == VISCOSITYMODEL::POLYNOMIAL)) {
5105  su2double sum = 0.0;
5106  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < N_POLY_COEFFS; iVar++) {
5107  sum += GetMu_PolyCoeff(iVar);
5108  }
5109  if ((N_POLY_COEFFS < 1) || (sum == 0.0))
5110  SU2_MPI::Error(string("MU_POLYCOEFFS not set for viscosity model POLYNOMIAL_VISCOSITY. \n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5111  }
5112 
5113  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) && (Kind_ConductivityModel == CONDUCTIVITYMODEL::POLYNOMIAL)) {
5114  su2double sum = 0.0;
5115  for (unsigned short iVar = 0; iVar < N_POLY_COEFFS; iVar++) {
5116  sum += GetKt_PolyCoeff(iVar);
5117  }
5118  if ((N_POLY_COEFFS < 1) || (sum == 0.0))
5119  SU2_MPI::Error(string("KT_POLYCOEFFS not set for conductivity model POLYNOMIAL_CONDUCTIVITY. \n"), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5120  }
5121 
5122  /*--- Incompressible solver currently limited to SI units. ---*/
5123 
5124  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) && (SystemMeasurements == US)) {
5125  SU2_MPI::Error("Must use SI units for incompressible solver.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5126  }
5127 
5128  /*--- Check that the non-dim type is valid. ---*/
5129 
5130  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS)) {
5131  if ((Ref_Inc_NonDim != INITIAL_VALUES) && (Ref_Inc_NonDim != REFERENCE_VALUES) && (Ref_Inc_NonDim != DIMENSIONAL)) {
5132  SU2_MPI::Error("Incompressible non-dim. scheme invalid.\n Must use INITIAL_VALUES, REFERENCE_VALUES, or DIMENSIONAL.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5133  }
5134  }
5135 
5136  /*--- Check that the incompressible inlets are correctly specified. ---*/
5137 
5138  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) && (nMarker_Inlet != 0)) {
5139  if (nMarker_Inlet != nInc_Inlet) {
5140  SU2_MPI::Error("Inlet types for incompressible problem improperly specified.\n Use INC_INLET_TYPE= VELOCITY_INLET or PRESSURE_INLET.\n Must list a type for each inlet marker, including duplicates, e.g.,\n INC_INLET_TYPE= VELOCITY_INLET VELOCITY_INLET PRESSURE_INLET", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5141  }
5142  for (unsigned short iInlet = 0; iInlet < nInc_Inlet; iInlet++){
5143  if ((Kind_Inc_Inlet[iInlet] != INLET_TYPE::VELOCITY_INLET) && (Kind_Inc_Inlet[iInlet] != INLET_TYPE::PRESSURE_INLET)) {
5144  SU2_MPI::Error("Undefined incompressible inlet type. VELOCITY_INLET or PRESSURE_INLET possible.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5145  }
5146  }
5147  }
5148 
5149  /*--- Check that the incompressible inlets are correctly specified. ---*/
5150 
5151  if ((Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES || Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) && (nMarker_Outlet != 0)) {
5152  if (nMarker_Outlet != nInc_Outlet) {
5153  SU2_MPI::Error("Outlet types for incompressible problem improperly specified.\n Use INC_OUTLET_TYPE= PRESSURE_OUTLET or MASS_FLOW_OUTLET.\n Must list a type for each inlet marker, including duplicates, e.g.,\n INC_OUTLET_TYPE= PRESSURE_OUTLET PRESSURE_OUTLET MASS_FLOW_OUTLET", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5154  }
5155  for (unsigned short iInlet = 0; iInlet < nInc_Outlet; iInlet++){
5156  if ((Kind_Inc_Outlet[iInlet] != INC_OUTLET_TYPE::PRESSURE_OUTLET) && (Kind_Inc_Outlet[iInlet] != INC_OUTLET_TYPE::MASS_FLOW_OUTLET)) {
5157  SU2_MPI::Error("Undefined incompressible outlet type. PRESSURE_OUTLET or MASS_FLOW_OUTLET possible.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5158  }
5159  }
5160  }
5161 
5162  /*--- Assert that there are two markers being analyzed if the
5163  pressure drop objective function is selected. ---*/
5164 
5165  for (unsigned short iObj = 0; iObj < nObj; iObj++) {
5166  if ((Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] == SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP) && (nMarker_Analyze < 2)) {
5167  SU2_MPI::Error("Must list the first two markers for the pressure drop objective function.\n Expected format: MARKER_ANALYZE= (outlet_name, inlet_name, ...).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5168  }
5169  }
5170 
5171  /*--- Check feasibility for Streamwise Periodic flow ---*/
5172  if (Kind_Streamwise_Periodic != ENUM_STREAMWISE_PERIODIC::NONE) {
5173  if (Kind_Regime != ENUM_REGIME::INCOMPRESSIBLE)
5174  SU2_MPI::Error("Streamwise Periodic Flow currently only implemented for incompressible flow.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5175  if (Kind_Solver == MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER)
5176  SU2_MPI::Error("Streamwise Periodic Flow + Incompressible Euler: Not tested yet.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5177  if (nMarker_PerBound == 0)
5178  SU2_MPI::Error("A MARKER_PERIODIC pair has to be set with KIND_STREAMWISE_PERIODIC != NONE.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5179  if (Energy_Equation && Streamwise_Periodic_Temperature && nMarker_Isothermal != 0)
5180  SU2_MPI::Error("No MARKER_ISOTHERMAL marker allowed with STREAMWISE_PERIODIC_TEMPERATURE= YES, only MARKER_HEATFLUX & MARKER_SYM.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5181  if (Ref_Inc_NonDim != DIMENSIONAL)
5182  SU2_MPI::Error("Streamwise Periodicity only works with \"INC_NONDIM= DIMENSIONAL\", the nondimensionalization with source terms doesn;t work in general.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5183  if (Axisymmetric)
5184  SU2_MPI::Error("Streamwise Periodicity terms does not not have axisymmetric corrections.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5185  if (!Energy_Equation) Streamwise_Periodic_Temperature = false;
5186  } else {
5187  /*--- Safety measure ---*/
5188  Streamwise_Periodic_Temperature = false;
5189  }
5190 
5191  if (nRough_Wall > 0) {
5192  /*--- Validate name of the markers. ---*/
5193  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nRough_Wall; ++iMarker) {
5194  auto CheckMarker = [&](unsigned short nMarker, const string* markerName) {
5195  for (auto jMarker = 0u; jMarker < nMarker; ++jMarker) {
5196  if (markerName[jMarker].compare(Marker_RoughWall[iMarker]) == 0) {
5197  return true;
5198  }
5199  }
5200  return false;
5201  };
5202  if (!CheckMarker(nMarker_HeatFlux, Marker_HeatFlux) &&
5203  !CheckMarker(nMarker_Isothermal, Marker_Isothermal) &&
5204  !CheckMarker(nMarker_HeatTransfer, Marker_HeatTransfer) &&
5205  !CheckMarker(nMarker_CHTInterface, Marker_CHTInterface)) {
5206  SU2_MPI::Error("Marker " + Marker_RoughWall[iMarker] + " is not a viscous wall.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5207  }
5208  }
5209  }
5210 
5211  /*--- Handle default options for topology optimization ---*/
5212 
5213  if (topology_optimization && top_optim_nKernel==0) {
5214  top_optim_nKernel = 1;
5215  top_optim_kernels = new ENUM_FILTER_KERNEL [1];
5216  top_optim_kernels[0] = ENUM_FILTER_KERNEL::CONICAL_WEIGHT;
5217  }
5218 
5219  if (top_optim_nKernel != 0) {
5220  /*--- Set default value of kernel parameters ---*/
5221  if (top_optim_nKernelParams == 0) {
5222  top_optim_nKernelParams = top_optim_nKernel;
5223  top_optim_kernel_params = new su2double [top_optim_nKernel];
5224  for (unsigned short i=0; i<top_optim_nKernel; ++i) top_optim_kernel_params[i] = 1.0;
5225  }
5226  /*--- Broadcast the only value provided ---*/
5227  else if (top_optim_nKernelParams==1 && top_optim_nKernel>1) {
5228  su2double tmp = top_optim_kernel_params[0];
5229  delete [] top_optim_kernel_params;
5230  top_optim_nKernelParams = top_optim_nKernel;
5231  top_optim_kernel_params = new su2double [top_optim_nKernel];
5232  for (unsigned short i=0; i<top_optim_nKernel; ++i) top_optim_kernel_params[i] = tmp;
5233  }
5234  /*--- Numbers do not match ---*/
5235  else if (top_optim_nKernelParams != top_optim_nKernel) {
5236  SU2_MPI::Error("Different number of topology filter kernels and respective parameters.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5237  }
5238 
5239  /*--- Set default value of filter radius ---*/
5240  if (top_optim_nRadius == 0) {
5241  top_optim_nRadius = top_optim_nKernel;
5242  top_optim_filter_radius = new su2double [top_optim_nKernel];
5243  for (unsigned short i=0; i<top_optim_nKernel; ++i) top_optim_filter_radius[i] = 1.0e-6;
5244  }
5245  /*--- Broadcast the only value provided ---*/
5246  else if (top_optim_nRadius==1 && top_optim_nKernel>1) {
5247  su2double tmp = top_optim_filter_radius[0];
5248  delete [] top_optim_filter_radius;
5249  top_optim_nRadius = top_optim_nKernel;
5250  top_optim_filter_radius = new su2double [top_optim_nKernel];
5251  for (unsigned short i=0; i<top_optim_nKernel; ++i) top_optim_filter_radius[i] = tmp;
5252  }
5253  /*--- Numbers do not match ---*/
5254  else if (top_optim_nRadius != top_optim_nKernel) {
5255  SU2_MPI::Error("Different number of topology filter kernels and respective radii.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5256  }
5257  }
5258 
5259  /*--- If we are executing SU2_DOT in surface file mode, then
5260  force the projected surface sensitivity file to be written. ---*/
5261 
5262  Wrt_Projected_Sensitivity = false;
5263  if ((Kind_SU2 == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_DOT) && (Design_Variable[0] == SURFACE_FILE)) {
5264  Wrt_Projected_Sensitivity = true;
5265  }
5266 
5267  /*--- Delay the output until exit for minimal communication mode. ---*/
5268 
5269  if (Comm_Level != COMM_FULL) {
5270 
5271  /*--- Disable the use of Comm_Level = NONE until we have properly
5272  implemented it. ---*/
5273 
5274  if (Comm_Level == COMM_NONE)
5275  SU2_MPI::Error("COMM_LEVEL = NONE not yet implemented.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5276  }
5277 
5278  /*--- Check the conductivity model. Deactivate the turbulent component
5279  if we are not running RANS. ---*/
5280 
5281  if ((Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::RANS) &&
5282  (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_RANS) &&
5283  (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS) &&
5284  (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS) &&
5285  (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS)){
5286  Kind_ConductivityModel_Turb = CONDUCTIVITYMODEL_TURB::NONE;
5287  }
5288 
5289  /* Set a default for the size of the RECTANGLE / BOX grid sizes. */
5290 
5291  if (nMesh_Box_Size == 0) {
5292  nMesh_Box_Size = 3;
5293  Mesh_Box_Size = new short [nMesh_Box_Size];
5294  Mesh_Box_Size[0] = 33;
5295  Mesh_Box_Size[1] = 33;
5296  Mesh_Box_Size[2] = 33;
5297  } else if (nMesh_Box_Size != 3) {
5298  SU2_MPI::Error("MESH_BOX_SIZE specified without 3 values.\n", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5299  }
5300 
5301  /* Force the lowest memory preconditioner when direct solvers are used. */
5302 
5303  auto isPastix = [](unsigned short kindSolver) {
5304  return kindSolver == PASTIX_LDLT || kindSolver == PASTIX_LU;
5305  };
5306 
5307  if (isPastix(Kind_Linear_Solver)) Kind_Linear_Solver_Prec = LU_SGS;
5308  if (isPastix(Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Solver)) Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Prec = LU_SGS;
5309  if (isPastix(Kind_Deform_Linear_Solver)) Kind_Deform_Linear_Solver_Prec = LU_SGS;
5310 
5311 
5312  if (DiscreteAdjoint) {
5313 #if !defined CODI_REVERSE_TYPE
5314  if (Kind_SU2 == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_CFD) {
5315  SU2_MPI::Error("SU2_CFD: Config option MATH_PROBLEM= DISCRETE_ADJOINT requires AD support!\n"
5316  "Please use SU2_CFD_AD (configuration/compilation is done using the preconfigure.py script).",
5317  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5318  }
5319 #endif
5320 
5321  /*--- Use the same linear solver on the primal as the one used in the adjoint. ---*/
5322  Kind_Linear_Solver = Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Solver;
5323  Kind_Linear_Solver_Prec = Kind_DiscAdj_Linear_Prec;
5324 
5325  if (Time_Domain) {
5326 
5327  Restart_Flow = false;
5328 
5329  if (Unst_AdjointIter- long(nTimeIter) < 0){
5330  SU2_MPI::Error("Invalid iteration number requested for unsteady adjoint.\n"
5331  "Make sure EXT_ITER is larger or equal than UNST_ADJOINT_ITER.",
5332  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5333  }
5334 
5335  /*--- If the averaging interval is not set, we average over all time-steps ---*/
5336 
5337  if (Iter_Avg_Objective == 0.0) {
5338  Iter_Avg_Objective = nTimeIter;
5339  }
5340 
5341  }
5342 
5343  /*--- Note that this is deliberately done at the end of this routine! ---*/
5344  switch(Kind_Solver) {
5345  case MAIN_SOLVER::EULER:
5346  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_EULER;
5347  break;
5348  case MAIN_SOLVER::RANS:
5349  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS;
5350  break;
5351  case MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES:
5352  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES;
5353  break;
5354  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER:
5355  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_EULER;
5356  break;
5357  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS:
5358  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS;
5359  break;
5360  case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES:
5361  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES;
5362  break;
5363  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER :
5364  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_EULER;
5365  break;
5366  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS :
5367  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_RANS;
5368  break;
5369  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES :
5370  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_NS;
5371  break;
5372  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY:
5373  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM;
5374  break;
5375  case MAIN_SOLVER::HEAT_EQUATION:
5376  Kind_Solver = MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_HEAT;
5377  break;
5378  default:
5379  break;
5380  }
5381 
5382  RampOutletPressure = false;
5383  RampRotatingFrame = false;
5384  }
5385 
5386  /* 2nd-order MUSCL is not possible for the continuous adjoint
5387  turbulence model. */
5388 
5389  if (MUSCL_AdjTurb) {
5390  SU2_MPI::Error("MUSCL_ADJTURB= YES not currently supported.\nPlease select MUSCL_ADJTURB= NO (first-order).",
5391  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5392  }
5393 
5394  /* Check for whether we need a second gradient method to calculate
5395  gradients for uwpind reconstruction. Set additional booleans to
5396  minimize overhead as appropriate. */
5397 
5398  if (MUSCL_Flow || MUSCL_Turb || MUSCL_Species || MUSCL_Heat || MUSCL_AdjFlow) {
5399 
5400  ReconstructionGradientRequired = true;
5401 
5402  if ((Kind_Gradient_Method_Recon == NO_GRADIENT) ||
5403  (Kind_Gradient_Method_Recon == Kind_Gradient_Method)) {
5404 
5405  /* The default behavior if no reconstruction gradient is specified
5406  is to use the same gradient as needed for the viscous/source terms
5407  without recomputation. If they are using the same method, then
5408  we also want to avoid recomputation. */
5409 
5410  ReconstructionGradientRequired = false;
5411  Kind_Gradient_Method_Recon = Kind_Gradient_Method;
5412  }
5413 
5414  } else {
5415  ReconstructionGradientRequired = false;
5416  }
5417 
5418  if (ReconstructionGradientRequired && GetFluidProblem() && Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow == SPACE_CENTERED)
5419  SU2_MPI::Error("For centered schemes the option NUM_METHOD_GRAD_RECON should not be set.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5420 
5421  /* Simpler boolean to control allocation of least-squares memory. */
5422 
5423  LeastSquaresRequired = false;
5424  if ((Kind_Gradient_Method_Recon == LEAST_SQUARES) ||
5425  (Kind_Gradient_Method_Recon == WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES) ||
5426  (Kind_Gradient_Method == LEAST_SQUARES) ||
5427  (Kind_Gradient_Method == WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES)) {
5428  LeastSquaresRequired = true;
5429  }
5430 
5431  if (Kind_Gradient_Method == LEAST_SQUARES) {
5432  SU2_MPI::Error(string("LEAST_SQUARES gradient method not allowed for viscous / source terms.\n") +
5433  string("Please select either WEIGHTED_LEAST_SQUARES or GREEN_GAUSS."),
5434  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5435  }
5436 
5437  /* Protect against using CFL adaption for non-flow or certain
5438  unsteady flow problems. */
5439 
5440  if (CFL_Adapt && !GetFluidProblem()) {
5441  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CFL adaption only available for finite-volume fluid solvers.\n") +
5442  string("Please select CFL_ADAPT = NO."),
5443  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5444  }
5445 
5446  if (CFL_Adapt && (TimeMarching == TIME_MARCHING::TIME_STEPPING)) {
5447  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CFL adaption not available for TIME_STEPPING integration.\n") +
5448  string("Please select CFL_ADAPT = NO."),
5449  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5450  }
5451 
5452  /* Protect against using incorrect CFL adaption parameters. */
5453 
5454  if (CFL_Adapt && (CFL_AdaptParam[0] > 1.0)) {
5455  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CFL adaption factor down should be less than 1.0."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5456  }
5457 
5458  if (CFL_Adapt && (CFL_AdaptParam[1] < 1.0)) {
5459  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CFL adaption factor up should be greater than 1.0."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5460  }
5461 
5462  if (CFL_Adapt && (CFL_AdaptParam[2] > CFL_AdaptParam[3])) {
5463  SU2_MPI::Error(string("CFL adaption minimum CFL is larger than the maximum CFL."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5464  }
5465 
5466  /*--- 0 in the config file means "disable" which can be done using a very large group. ---*/
5467  if (edgeColorGroupSize==0) edgeColorGroupSize = 1<<30;
5468 
5469  /*--- Specifying a deforming surface requires a mesh deformation solver. ---*/
5470  if (GetSurface_Movement(DEFORMING)) Deform_Mesh = true;
5471 
5472  monoatomic = GetGasModel() == "ARGON";
5473 
5474  /*--- Set number of Turbulence Variables. ---*/
5475  switch (TurbModelFamily(Kind_Turb_Model)) {
5476  case TURB_FAMILY::NONE:
5477  nTurbVar = 0; break;
5478  case TURB_FAMILY::SA:
5479  nTurbVar = 1; break;
5480  case TURB_FAMILY::KW:
5481  nTurbVar = 2; break;
5482  }
5483  /*--- Check whether the number of entries of the MARKER_INLET_TURBULENT equals the number of turbulent properties
5484  used for the respective turbulent model. nTurb_Properties must be equal to 1 or 2 depending on whether SA or
5485  SST model are used.--- */
5486  if (Marker_Inlet_Turb != nullptr && Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SST && nTurb_Properties != 2)
5487  SU2_MPI::Error(
5488  "The use of MARKER_INLET_TURBULENT requires the number of entries when SST Model is used \n"
5489  "to be equal to 2 : Turbulent intensity and ratio turbulent to laminar viscosity",
5490  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5491  if (Marker_Inlet_Turb != nullptr && Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SA && nTurb_Properties != 1)
5492  SU2_MPI::Error(
5493  "The use of MARKER_INLET_TURBULENT requires the number of entries when SA Model is used \n"
5494  "to be equal to 1 : ratio turbulent to laminar viscosity",
5495  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5496 
5497  /*--- Checks for additional species transport. ---*/
5498  if ((Kind_Species_Model == SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT) || (Kind_Species_Model == SPECIES_MODEL::FLAMELET)) {
5499  if (Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES &&
5500  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS &&
5501  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES &&
5502  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS &&
5503  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES &&
5504  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::RANS &&
5505  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES &&
5506  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS &&
5507  Kind_Solver != MAIN_SOLVER::MULTIPHYSICS)
5508  SU2_MPI::Error("Species transport currently only available for compressible and incompressible flow.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5509 
5510  /*--- Species specific OF currently can only handle one entry in Marker_Analyze. ---*/
5511  for (unsigned short iObj = 0; iObj < nObj; iObj++) {
5512  if ((Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] == SURFACE_SPECIES_0 ||
5513  Kind_ObjFunc[iObj] == SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE) &&
5514  nMarker_Analyze > 1) {
5515  SU2_MPI::Error("SURFACE_SPECIES_0 and SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE currently can only handle one entry to MARKER_ANALYZE.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5516  }
5517  }
5518 
5519  if(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Species != EULER_IMPLICIT &&
5520  Kind_TimeIntScheme_Species != EULER_EXPLICIT){
5521  SU2_MPI::Error("Only TIME_DISCRE_TURB = EULER_IMPLICIT, EULER_EXPLICIT have been implemented in the scalar solver.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5522  }
5523 
5524  /*--- If Species clipping is on, make sure bounds are given by the user. ---*/
5525  if (Species_Clipping)
5526  if (!(OptionIsSet("SPECIES_CLIPPING_MIN") && OptionIsSet("SPECIES_CLIPPING_MAX")))
5527  SU2_MPI::Error("SPECIES_CLIPPING= YES requires the options SPECIES_CLIPPING_MIN/MAX to set the clipping values.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5528 
5529  /*--- Make sure a Diffusivity has been set for Constant Diffusivity. ---*/
5530  if (Kind_Diffusivity_Model == DIFFUSIVITYMODEL::CONSTANT_DIFFUSIVITY &&
5531  !(OptionIsSet("DIFFUSIVITY_CONSTANT")))
5532  SU2_MPI::Error("A DIFFUSIVITY_CONSTANT=<value> has to be set with DIFFUSIVITY_MODEL= CONSTANT_DIFFUSIVITY.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5533 
5534  /*--- Check whether the number of entries of the constant Lewis number equals the number of transported scalar
5535  equations solved. nConstant_Lewis_Number is used because it is required for the diffusivity fluid mixing
5536  models--- */
5537  if (Kind_Diffusivity_Model == DIFFUSIVITYMODEL::CONSTANT_LEWIS && nConstant_Lewis_Number != nSpecies_Init + 1)
5538  SU2_MPI::Error(
5539  "The use of CONSTANT_LEWIS requires the number of entries for CONSTANT_LEWIS_NUMBER ,\n"
5540  "to be equal to the number of entries of SPECIES_INIT +1",
5541  CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5542 
5543  // Helper function that checks scalar variable bounds,
5544  auto checkScalarBounds = [&](su2double scalar, const string& name, su2double lowerBound, su2double upperBound) {
5545  if (scalar < lowerBound || scalar > upperBound)
5546  SU2_MPI::Error(string("Variable: ") + name + string(", is out of bounds."), CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5547  };
5548 
5549  /*--- Some options have to provide as many entries as there are additional species equations. ---*/
5550  /*--- Fill a vector with the entires and then check if each element is equal to the first one. ---*/
5551  std::vector<unsigned short> nSpecies_options;
5552  nSpecies_options.push_back(nSpecies_Init);
5553  if (Species_Clipping)
5554  nSpecies_options.insert(nSpecies_options.end(), {nSpecies_Clipping_Min, nSpecies_Clipping_Max});
5555  if (nMarker_Inlet_Species > 0)
5556  nSpecies_options.push_back(nSpecies_per_Inlet);
5557  // Add more options for size check here.
5558 
5559  /*--- nSpecies_Init is the master, but it simply checks for consistency. ---*/
5560  for (auto elem : nSpecies_options)
5561  if (nSpecies_options[0] != elem)
5562  SU2_MPI::Error("Make sure all species inputs have the same size.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5563 
5564  /*--- Once consistency is checked set the var that is used throughout the code. ---*/
5565  nSpecies = nSpecies_Init;
5566 
5567  /*--- Check whether some variables (or their sums) are in physical bounds. [0,1] for species related quantities. ---*/
5568  /*--- Note, only for species transport, not for flamelet model ---*/
5569  if (Kind_Species_Model == SPECIES_MODEL::SPECIES_TRANSPORT) {
5570  su2double Species_Init_Sum = 0.0;
5571  for (unsigned short iSpecies = 0; iSpecies < nSpecies; iSpecies++) {
5572  checkScalarBounds(Species_Init[iSpecies], "SPECIES_INIT individual", 0.0, 1.0);
5573  Species_Init_Sum += Species_Init[iSpecies];
5574  }
5575  checkScalarBounds(Species_Init_Sum, "SPECIES_INIT sum", 0.0, 1.0);
5576 
5577  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Inlet_Species; iMarker++) {
5578  su2double Inlet_SpeciesVal_Sum = 0.0;
5579  for (unsigned short iSpecies = 0; iSpecies < nSpecies; iSpecies++) {
5580  checkScalarBounds(Inlet_SpeciesVal[iMarker][iSpecies], "MARKER_INLET_SPECIES individual", 0.0, 1.0);
5581  Inlet_SpeciesVal_Sum += Inlet_SpeciesVal[iMarker][iSpecies];
5582  }
5583  checkScalarBounds(Inlet_SpeciesVal_Sum, "MARKER_INLET_SPECIES sum", 0.0, 1.0);
5584  }
5585  }
5586 
5587  } // species transport checks
5588 
5589  /*--- Define some variables for flamelet model. ---*/
5590  if (Kind_Species_Model == SPECIES_MODEL::FLAMELET) {
5591  /*--- The controlling variables are progress variable, total enthalpy, and optionally mixture fraction ---*/
5592  //n_control_vars = nSpecies - n_user_scalars;
5593  if (n_control_vars != (nSpecies - n_user_scalars))
5594  SU2_MPI::Error("Number of initial species incompatbile with number of controlling variables and user scalars.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5595  /*--- We can have additional user defined transported scalars ---*/
5596  n_scalars = n_control_vars + n_user_scalars;
5597  }
5598 
5599  if (Kind_Regime == ENUM_REGIME::COMPRESSIBLE && GetBounded_Scalar()) {
5600  SU2_MPI::Error("BOUNDED_SCALAR discretization can only be used for incompressible problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
5601  }
5602 }
5603 
5604 void CConfig::SetMarkers(SU2_COMPONENT val_software) {
5605 
5606  unsigned short iMarker_All, iMarker_CfgFile, iMarker_Euler, iMarker_Custom,
5607  iMarker_FarField, iMarker_SymWall, iMarker_PerBound,
5608  iMarker_NearFieldBound, iMarker_Fluid_InterfaceBound,
5609  iMarker_Inlet, iMarker_Riemann, iMarker_Giles, iMarker_Outlet,
5610  iMarker_Smoluchowski_Maxwell,
5611  iMarker_Isothermal,iMarker_HeatFlux,iMarker_HeatTansfer,
5612  iMarker_EngineInflow, iMarker_EngineExhaust, iMarker_Damper,
5613  iMarker_Displacement, iMarker_Load, iMarker_Internal,
5614  iMarker_Monitoring, iMarker_Designing, iMarker_GeoEval, iMarker_Plotting, iMarker_Analyze,
5615  iMarker_DV, iMarker_Moving, iMarker_SobolevBC, iMarker_PyCustom, iMarker_Supersonic_Inlet, iMarker_Supersonic_Outlet,
5616  iMarker_Clamped, iMarker_ZoneInterface, iMarker_CHTInterface, iMarker_Load_Dir, iMarker_Disp_Dir,
5617  iMarker_Fluid_Load, iMarker_Deform_Mesh, iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane,
5618  iMarker_ActDiskInlet, iMarker_ActDiskOutlet,
5619  iMarker_Turbomachinery, iMarker_MixingPlaneInterface;
5620 
5621  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
5622  SU2_MPI::Comm_size(SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &size);
5623 
5624  /*--- Compute the total number of markers in the config file ---*/
5625  nMarker_CfgFile = nMarker_Euler + nMarker_FarField + nMarker_SymWall +
5626  nMarker_PerBound + nMarker_NearFieldBound + nMarker_Fluid_InterfaceBound +
5627  nMarker_CHTInterface + nMarker_Inlet + nMarker_Riemann + nMarker_Smoluchowski_Maxwell +
5628  nMarker_Giles + nMarker_Outlet + nMarker_Isothermal +
5629  nMarker_HeatFlux + nMarker_HeatTransfer +
5630  nMarker_EngineInflow + nMarker_EngineExhaust + nMarker_Internal +
5631  nMarker_Supersonic_Inlet + nMarker_Supersonic_Outlet + nMarker_Displacement + nMarker_Load +
5632  nMarker_Custom + nMarker_Damper + nMarker_Fluid_Load +
5633  nMarker_Clamped + nMarker_Load_Dir + nMarker_Disp_Dir +
5634  nMarker_ActDiskInlet + nMarker_ActDiskOutlet +
5635  nMarker_ActDiskBemInlet_CG + nMarker_ActDiskBemOutlet_CG +
5636  nMarker_ZoneInterface;
5637 
5638  /*--- Add the possible send/receive domains ---*/
5639 
5640  nMarker_Max = nMarker_CfgFile + OVERHEAD*size;
5641 
5642  /*--- Basic dimensionalization of the markers (worst scenario) ---*/
5643 
5644  nMarker_All = nMarker_Max;
5645 
5646  /*--- Allocate the memory (markers in each domain) ---*/
5647 
5648  Marker_All_TagBound = new string[nMarker_All]; // Store the tag that correspond with each marker.
5649  Marker_All_SendRecv = new short[nMarker_All] (); // +#domain (send), -#domain (receive).
5650  Marker_All_KindBC = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store the kind of boundary condition.
5651  Marker_All_Monitoring = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary should be monitored.
5652  Marker_All_Designing = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary should be designed.
5653  Marker_All_Plotting = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary should be plotted.
5654  Marker_All_Analyze = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary should be plotted.
5655  Marker_All_ZoneInterface = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary is in the FSI interface.
5656  Marker_All_GeoEval = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary should be geometry evaluation.
5657  Marker_All_DV = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary should be affected by design variables.
5658  Marker_All_Moving = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary should be in motion.
5659  Marker_All_Deform_Mesh = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary is deformable.
5660  Marker_All_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); //Store wheter the boundary will follow the deformation
5661  Marker_All_Fluid_Load = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary computes/applies fluid loads.
5662  Marker_All_PyCustom = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary is Python customizable.
5663  Marker_All_PerBound = new short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary belongs to a periodic boundary.
5664  Marker_All_Turbomachinery = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary is in needed for Turbomachinery computations.
5665  Marker_All_TurbomachineryFlag = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary has a flag for Turbomachinery computations.
5666  Marker_All_MixingPlaneInterface = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary has a in the MixingPlane interface.
5667  Marker_All_Giles = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store whether the boundary has is a Giles boundary.
5668  Marker_All_SobolevBC = new unsigned short[nMarker_All] (); // Store wether the boundary should apply to the gradient smoothing.
5669 
5670  for (iMarker_All = 0; iMarker_All < nMarker_All; iMarker_All++) {
5671  Marker_All_TagBound[iMarker_All] = "SEND_RECEIVE";
5672  }
5673 
5674  /*--- Allocate the memory (markers in the config file) ---*/
5675 
5676  Marker_CfgFile_TagBound = new string[nMarker_CfgFile];
5677  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5678  Marker_CfgFile_Monitoring = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5679  Marker_CfgFile_Designing = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5680  Marker_CfgFile_Plotting = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5681  Marker_CfgFile_Analyze = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5682  Marker_CfgFile_GeoEval = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5683  Marker_CfgFile_ZoneInterface = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5684  Marker_CfgFile_DV = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5685  Marker_CfgFile_Moving = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5686  Marker_CfgFile_Deform_Mesh = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5687  Marker_CfgFile_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane= new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5688  Marker_CfgFile_Fluid_Load = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5689  Marker_CfgFile_PerBound = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5690  Marker_CfgFile_Turbomachinery = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5691  Marker_CfgFile_TurbomachineryFlag = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5692  Marker_CfgFile_MixingPlaneInterface = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5693  Marker_CfgFile_Giles = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5694  Marker_CfgFile_PyCustom = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5695  Marker_CfgFile_SobolevBC = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile] ();
5696 
5697  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
5698  Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] = "SEND_RECEIVE";
5699  }
5700 
5701  /*--- Allocate memory to store surface information (Analyze BC) ---*/
5702 
5703  Surface_MassFlow = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5704  Surface_Mach = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5705  Surface_Temperature = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5706  Surface_Pressure = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5707  Surface_Density = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5708  Surface_Enthalpy = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5709  Surface_NormalVelocity = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5710  Surface_Uniformity = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5711  Surface_SecondaryStrength = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5712  Surface_SecondOverUniform = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5713  Surface_MomentumDistortion = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5714  Surface_TotalTemperature = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5715  Surface_TotalPressure = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5716  Surface_PressureDrop = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5717  Surface_Species_0 = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5718  Surface_Species_Variance = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5719  Surface_DC60 = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5720  Surface_IDC = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5721  Surface_IDC_Mach = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5722  Surface_IDR = new su2double[nMarker_Analyze] ();
5723 
5724  /*--- Populate the marker information in the config file (all domains) ---*/
5725 
5726  iMarker_CfgFile = 0;
5727  for (iMarker_Euler = 0; iMarker_Euler < nMarker_Euler; iMarker_Euler++) {
5728  Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] = Marker_Euler[iMarker_Euler];
5729  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = EULER_WALL;
5730  iMarker_CfgFile++;
5731  }
5732 
5733  for (iMarker_FarField = 0; iMarker_FarField < nMarker_FarField; iMarker_FarField++) {
5734  Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] = Marker_FarField[iMarker_FarField];
5735  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = FAR_FIELD;
5736  iMarker_CfgFile++;
5737  }
5738 
5739  for (iMarker_SymWall = 0; iMarker_SymWall < nMarker_SymWall; iMarker_SymWall++) {
5740  Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] = Marker_SymWall[iMarker_SymWall];
5741  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = SYMMETRY_PLANE;
5742  iMarker_CfgFile++;
5743  }
5744 
5745  for (iMarker_PerBound = 0; iMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; iMarker_PerBound++) {
5746  Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] = Marker_PerBound[iMarker_PerBound];
5747  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = PERIODIC_BOUNDARY;
5748  Marker_CfgFile_PerBound[iMarker_CfgFile] = iMarker_PerBound + 1;
5749  iMarker_CfgFile++;
5750  }
5751 
5752  ActDisk_DeltaPress = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5753  ActDisk_DeltaTemp = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5754  ActDisk_TotalPressRatio = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5755  ActDisk_TotalTempRatio = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5756  ActDisk_StaticPressRatio = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5757  ActDisk_StaticTempRatio = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5758  ActDisk_Power = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5759  ActDisk_MassFlow = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5760  ActDisk_Mach = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5761  ActDisk_Force = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5762  ActDisk_NetThrust = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5763  ActDisk_BCThrust = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5764  ActDisk_BCThrust_Old = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5765  ActDisk_GrossThrust = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5766  ActDisk_Area = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5767  ActDisk_ReverseMassFlow = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5768 
5769  ActDiskInlet_MassFlow = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5770  ActDiskInlet_Temperature = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5771  ActDiskInlet_TotalTemperature = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5772  ActDiskInlet_Pressure = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5773  ActDiskInlet_TotalPressure = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5774  ActDiskInlet_RamDrag = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5775  ActDiskInlet_Force = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5776  ActDiskInlet_Power = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskInlet] ();
5777 
5778  for (iMarker_ActDiskInlet = 0; iMarker_ActDiskInlet < nMarker_ActDiskInlet; iMarker_ActDiskInlet++) {
5779  Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] = Marker_ActDiskInlet[iMarker_ActDiskInlet];
5780  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = ACTDISK_INLET;
5781  iMarker_CfgFile++;
5782  }
5783 
5784  ActDiskOutlet_MassFlow = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskOutlet] ();

5792

5794  ActDiskOutlet_Torque_BEM = new su2double[nMarker_ActDiskOutlet]();
5795 
5796  for (iMarker_ActDiskOutlet = 0; iMarker_ActDiskOutlet < nMarker_ActDiskOutlet; iMarker_ActDiskOutlet++) {

5798  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = ACTDISK_OUTLET;

6026  for (iMarker_Turbomachinery = 0; iMarker_Turbomachinery < nMarker_Turbomachinery; iMarker_Turbomachinery++){
6027  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_TurboBoundIn[iMarker_Turbomachinery]){

6029  Marker_CfgFile_Turbomachinery[iMarker_CfgFile] = indexMarker;
6030  Marker_CfgFile_TurbomachineryFlag[iMarker_CfgFile] = INFLOW;
6031  }
6032  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_TurboBoundOut[iMarker_Turbomachinery]){
6033  indexMarker=(iMarker_Turbomachinery+1);
6034  Marker_CfgFile_Turbomachinery[iMarker_CfgFile] = indexMarker;
6035  Marker_CfgFile_TurbomachineryFlag[iMarker_CfgFile] = OUTFLOW;
6036  }
6037  }
6038  }

6041  // This is seperate from MP and Turbomachinery Markers as all mixing plane markers are Giles,
6042  // but not all Giles markers are mixing plane
6043  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {

6047  Marker_CfgFile_Giles[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
6048  }
6049  }

6052 
6053  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
6054  unsigned short indexMarker=0;
6055  Marker_CfgFile_MixingPlaneInterface[iMarker_CfgFile] = NO;
6056  for (iMarker_MixingPlaneInterface = 0; iMarker_MixingPlaneInterface < nMarker_MixingPlaneInterface; iMarker_MixingPlaneInterface++)
6057  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_MixingPlaneInterface[iMarker_MixingPlaneInterface])
6058  indexMarker=(int)(iMarker_MixingPlaneInterface/2+1);
6059  Marker_CfgFile_MixingPlaneInterface[iMarker_CfgFile] = indexMarker;
6060  }
6061 
6062  /*--- Once we have identified the MixingPlane and Turbomachinery markers
6063  * we next need to determine what type of interface between zones is
6064  * used. It is convenient to do this here as it tidies up the interface
6065  * preproccesing in CDriver ---*/
6066  if (nMarker_Turbomachinery != 0) {
6067  nTurboInterfaces = (nMarker_Turbomachinery - 1)*2; //Two markers per zone minus inlet & outlet
6068  Kind_TurboInterface.resize(nTurboInterfaces);
6069  /*--- Loop over all markers ---*/
6070  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
6071  /*--- Identify mixing plane markers ---*/
6072  if (Marker_MixingPlaneInterface != nullptr){ // Necessary in cases where no mixing plane interfaces are defined
6073  if (Marker_CfgFile_MixingPlaneInterface[iMarker_CfgFile] != 0) { //Is a mixing plane
6074  /*--- Find which list position this marker is in turbomachinery markers ---*/
6075  const auto* target = std::find(Marker_Turbomachinery, &Marker_Turbomachinery[nMarker_Turbomachinery*2-1], Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile]);
6076  const auto target_index = target - Marker_Turbomachinery;
6077  /*--- Assert that we find the marker within the turbomachienry markers ---*/
6078  assert(target != &Marker_Turbomachinery[nMarker_Turbomachinery*2-1]);
6079  /*--- Assign the correct interface ---*/
6080  Kind_TurboInterface[target_index-1] = TURBO_INTERFACE_KIND::MIXING_PLANE; // Need to subtract 1 from index as to not consider the inlet an interface
6081  }
6082  }
6083  if (Marker_Fluid_InterfaceBound != nullptr){ // No fluid interfaces are defined in the config file (nullptr if no interfaces defined)
6084  if (Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] == BC_TYPE::FLUID_INTERFACE) { // iMarker_CfgFile is a fluid interface
6085  const auto* target = std::find(Marker_Turbomachinery, &Marker_Turbomachinery[nMarker_Turbomachinery*2-1], Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile]);
6086  const auto target_index = target - Marker_Turbomachinery;
6087  Kind_TurboInterface[target_index-1] = TURBO_INTERFACE_KIND::FROZEN_ROTOR;
6088  }
6089  }
6090  }
6091  }
6092 
6093  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
6094  Marker_CfgFile_DV[iMarker_CfgFile] = NO;
6095  for (iMarker_DV = 0; iMarker_DV < nMarker_DV; iMarker_DV++)
6096  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_DV[iMarker_DV])
6097  Marker_CfgFile_DV[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
6098  }
6099 
6100  /*--- Add an extra check for DV_MARKER to make sure that any given marker
6101  * name is recognized as an existing boundary in the problem. ---*/
6102 
6103  for (iMarker_DV = 0; iMarker_DV < nMarker_DV; iMarker_DV++) {
6104  bool found = false;
6105  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
6106  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_DV[iMarker_DV]) {
6107  found = true;
6108  break;
6109  }
6110  }
6111 
6112  if(!found) {
6113  if (nZone==1)
6114  SU2_MPI::Error("DV_MARKER contains marker names that do not exist in the lists of BCs in the config file.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
6115  // In case of multiple zones, the markers might appear only in zonal config and not in the Master.
6116  // A loop over all zones would need to be included which is not straight forward as this can only be
6117  // checked once all zonal configs are read.
6118  else if (rank == MASTER_NODE)
6119  cout << "Warning: DV_MARKER contains marker names that do not exist in the lists of BCs of the master config file.\n"
6120  "Make sure the marker names exist in the zonal config files" << endl;
6121  }
6122  }
6123 
6124  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
6125  Marker_CfgFile_Moving[iMarker_CfgFile] = NO;
6126  for (iMarker_Moving = 0; iMarker_Moving < nMarker_Moving; iMarker_Moving++)
6127  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_Moving[iMarker_Moving])
6128  Marker_CfgFile_Moving[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
6129  }
6130 
6131  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
6132  Marker_CfgFile_Deform_Mesh[iMarker_CfgFile] = NO;
6133  for (iMarker_Deform_Mesh = 0; iMarker_Deform_Mesh < nMarker_Deform_Mesh; iMarker_Deform_Mesh++)
6134  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_Deform_Mesh[iMarker_Deform_Mesh])
6135  Marker_CfgFile_Deform_Mesh[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
6136  }
6137 
6138  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
6139  Marker_CfgFile_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane[iMarker_CfgFile] = NO;
6140  for (iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane = 0; iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane < nMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane; iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane++)
6141  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane[iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane])
6142  Marker_CfgFile_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
6143  }
6144 
6145  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
6146  Marker_CfgFile_Fluid_Load[iMarker_CfgFile] = NO;
6147  for (iMarker_Fluid_Load = 0; iMarker_Fluid_Load < nMarker_Fluid_Load; iMarker_Fluid_Load++)
6148  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_Fluid_Load[iMarker_Fluid_Load])
6149  Marker_CfgFile_Fluid_Load[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
6150  }
6151 
6152  for (iMarker_CfgFile=0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
6153  Marker_CfgFile_PyCustom[iMarker_CfgFile] = NO;
6154  for(iMarker_PyCustom=0; iMarker_PyCustom < nMarker_PyCustom; iMarker_PyCustom++)
6155  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_PyCustom[iMarker_PyCustom])
6156  Marker_CfgFile_PyCustom[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
6157  }
6158 
6159  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
6160  Marker_CfgFile_SobolevBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = NO;
6161  for (iMarker_SobolevBC = 0; iMarker_SobolevBC < nMarker_SobolevBC; iMarker_SobolevBC++)
6162  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == Marker_SobolevBC[iMarker_SobolevBC])
6163  Marker_CfgFile_SobolevBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = YES;
6164  }
6165 
6166 }

6168 void CConfig::SetOutput(SU2_COMPONENT val_software, unsigned short val_izone) {
6169 
6170  unsigned short iMarker_Euler, iMarker_Custom, iMarker_FarField,
6171  iMarker_SymWall, iMarker_PerBound, iMarker_NearFieldBound,
6172  iMarker_Fluid_InterfaceBound, iMarker_Inlet, iMarker_Riemann,
6173  iMarker_Deform_Mesh, iMarker_Deform_Mesh_Sym_Plane, iMarker_Fluid_Load,
6174  iMarker_Smoluchowski_Maxwell, iWall_Catalytic,
6175  iMarker_Giles, iMarker_Outlet, iMarker_Isothermal, iMarker_HeatFlux, iMarker_HeatTransfer,
6176  iMarker_EngineInflow, iMarker_EngineExhaust, iMarker_Displacement, iMarker_Damper,
6177  iMarker_Load, iMarker_Internal, iMarker_Monitoring,
6178  iMarker_Designing, iMarker_GeoEval, iMarker_Plotting, iMarker_Analyze, iMarker_DV, iDV_Value,
6179  iMarker_ZoneInterface, iMarker_PyCustom, iMarker_Load_Dir, iMarker_Disp_Dir, iMarker_Clamped,

7745 bool CConfig::TokenizeString(string & str, string & option_name,
7746  vector<string> & option_value) {
7747  const string delimiters(" (){}:,\t\n\v\f\r");
7748  // check for comments or empty string
7749  string::size_type pos, last_pos;
7750  pos = str.find_first_of('%');
7751  if ( (str.length() == 0) || (pos == 0) ) {
7752  // str is empty or a comment line, so no option here
7753  return false;
7754  }
7755  if (pos != string::npos) {
7756  // remove comment at end if necessary
7757  str.erase(pos);
7758  }
7759 
7760  // look for line composed on only delimiters (usually whitespace)
7761  pos = str.find_first_not_of(delimiters);
7762  if (pos == string::npos) {
7763  return false;
7764  }
7765 
7766  // find the equals sign and split string
7767  string name_part, value_part;
7768  pos = str.find('=');
7769  if (pos == string::npos) {
7770  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
7771  << "line in the configuration file with no \"=\" sign."
7772  << endl;
7773  cout << "Look for: " << str << endl;
7774  cout << "str.length() = " << str.length() << endl;
7775  throw(-1);
7776  }
7777  name_part = str.substr(0, pos);
7778  value_part = str.substr(pos+1, string::npos);
7779  //cout << "name_part = |" << name_part << "|" << endl;
7780  //cout << "value_part = |" << value_part << "|" << endl;
7781 
7782  // the first_part should consist of one string with no interior delimiters
7783  last_pos = name_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, 0);
7784  pos = name_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
7785  if ( (name_part.length() == 0) || (last_pos == string::npos) ) {
7786  cerr << "Error in CConfig::TokenizeString(): "
7787  << "line in the configuration file with no name before the \"=\" sign."
7788  << endl;
7789  throw(-1);
7790  }
7791  if (pos == string::npos) pos = name_part.length();
7792  option_name = name_part.substr(last_pos, pos - last_pos);
7793  last_pos = name_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, pos);
7794  if (last_pos != string::npos) {
7795  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
7796  << "two or more options before an \"=\" sign in the configuration file."
7797  << endl;
7798  throw(-1);
7799  }
7800  StringToUpperCase(option_name);
7801 
7802  //cout << "option_name = |" << option_name << "|" << endl;
7803  //cout << "pos = " << pos << ": last_pos = " << last_pos << endl;
7804 
7805  // now fill the option value vector
7806  option_value.clear();
7807  last_pos = value_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, 0);
7808 
7809  // detect a raw string
7810  if (value_part[last_pos] == '\'' && value_part.back() == '\'') {
7811  option_value.push_back(value_part.substr(last_pos+1, value_part.size()-last_pos-2));
7812  return true;
7813  }
7814 
7815  pos = value_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
7816  while (string::npos != pos || string::npos != last_pos) {
7817  // add token to the vector<string>
7818  option_value.push_back(value_part.substr(last_pos, pos - last_pos));
7819  // skip delimiters
7820  last_pos = value_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, pos);
7821  // find next "non-delimiter"
7822  pos = value_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
7823  }
7824  if (option_value.empty()) {
7825  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
7826  << "option " << option_name << " in configuration file with no value assigned."
7827  << endl;
7828  throw(-1);
7829  }
7830 
7831 #if 0
7832  cout << "option value(s) = ";
7833  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
7834  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
7835  cout << endl;
7836 #endif
7837 
7838  // look for ';' DV delimiters attached to values
7839  vector<string>::iterator it;
7840  it = option_value.begin();
7841  while (it != option_value.end()) {
7842  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
7843  it++;
7844  continue;
7845  }
7846 
7847  pos = it->find(';');
7848  if (pos != string::npos) {
7849  string before_semi = it->substr(0, pos);
7850  string after_semi= it->substr(pos+1, string::npos);
7851  if (before_semi.empty()) {
7852  *it = ";";
7853  it++;
7854  option_value.insert(it, after_semi);
7855  } else {
7856  *it = before_semi;
7857  it++;
7858  vector<string> to_insert;
7859  to_insert.emplace_back(";");
7860  if (!after_semi.empty())
7861  to_insert.push_back(after_semi);
7862  option_value.insert(it, to_insert.begin(), to_insert.end());
7863  }
7864  it = option_value.begin(); // go back to beginning; not efficient
7865  continue;
7866  } it++;
7867 
7868  }
7869 #if 0
7870  cout << "option value(s) = ";
7871  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
7872  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
7873  cout << endl;
7874 #endif
7875  // remove any consecutive ";"
7876  it = option_value.begin();
7877  bool semi_at_prev = false;
7878  while (it != option_value.end()) {
7879  if (semi_at_prev) {
7880  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
7881  option_value.erase(it);
7882  it = option_value.begin();
7883  semi_at_prev = false;
7884  continue;
7885  }
7886  }
7887  semi_at_prev = it->compare(";") == 0;
7888  it++;
7889  }
7890 
7891 #if 0
7892  cout << "option value(s) = ";
7893  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
7894  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
7895  cout << endl;
7896 #endif
7897  return true;
7898 }
7899 
7900 unsigned short CConfig::GetMarker_CfgFile_TagBound(const string& val_marker) const {
7901 
7902  unsigned short iMarker_CfgFile;
7903 
7904  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
7905  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == val_marker)
7906  return iMarker_CfgFile;
7907  }
7908  SU2_MPI::Error(string("The configuration file doesn't have any definition for marker ") + val_marker, CURRENT_FUNCTION);
7909  return 0;
7910 }

8082 void CConfig::SetSurface_Movement(unsigned short iMarker, unsigned short kind_movement) {
8083 
8084  auto* new_surface_movement = new unsigned short[nMarker_Moving + 1];
8085  auto* new_marker_moving = new string[nMarker_Moving+1];
8086 
8087  for (unsigned short iMarker_Moving = 0; iMarker_Moving < nMarker_Moving; iMarker_Moving++){
8088  new_surface_movement[iMarker_Moving] = Kind_SurfaceMovement[iMarker_Moving];
8089  new_marker_moving[iMarker_Moving] = Marker_Moving[iMarker_Moving];
8090  }
8091 
8092  if (nKind_SurfaceMovement > 0){
8093  delete [] Marker_Moving;
8094  delete [] Kind_SurfaceMovement;
8095  }
8096 
8097  Kind_SurfaceMovement = new_surface_movement;
8098  Marker_Moving = new_marker_moving;
8099 
8100  Kind_SurfaceMovement[nMarker_Moving] = kind_movement;
8101  Marker_Moving[nMarker_Moving] = Marker_All_TagBound[iMarker];
8102 
8103  nMarker_Moving++;
8104  nKind_SurfaceMovement++;
8105 
8106 }

8330 
8331 string CConfig::GetFilename(string filename, const string& ext, int timeIter) const {
8332 
8333  /*--- Remove any extension --- */
8334 
8335  unsigned short lastindex = filename.find_last_of('.');
8336  filename = filename.substr(0, lastindex);
8337 
8338  /*--- Add the extension --- */
8339 
8340  filename = filename + string(ext);
8341 
8342  /*--- Append the zone number if multizone problems ---*/
8343  if (Multizone_Problem)
8344  filename = GetMultizone_FileName(filename, GetiZone(), ext);
8345 
8346  /*--- Append the zone number if multiple instance problems ---*/
8347  if (GetnTimeInstances() > 1)
8348  filename = GetMultiInstance_FileName(filename, GetiInst(), ext);
8349 
8350  /*--- Append the iteration number for unsteady problems ---*/
8351  if (GetTime_Domain()){
8352  filename = GetUnsteady_FileName(filename, timeIter, ext);
8353  }
8354 
8355  return filename;
8356 }
8357 
8358 string CConfig::GetFilename_Iter(const string& filename_iter, unsigned long curInnerIter, unsigned long curOuterIter) const {
8359  const auto iter = GetMultizone_Problem() ? curOuterIter : curInnerIter;
8360  std::stringstream iter_ss;
8361  iter_ss << filename_iter << "_" << std::setw(6) << std::setfill('0') << iter;
8362  return iter_ss.str();
8363 }
8364 
8365 string CConfig::GetUnsteady_FileName(string val_filename, int val_iter, const string& ext) const {
8366 
8367  string UnstExt, UnstFilename = std::move(val_filename);
8368  char buffer[50];
8369 
8370  /*--- Check that a positive value iteration is requested (for now). ---*/
8371 
8372  if (val_iter < 0) {
8373  SU2_MPI::Error("Requesting a negative iteration number for the restart file!!", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
8374  }
8375 
8376  unsigned short lastindex = UnstFilename.find_last_of('.');
8377  UnstFilename = UnstFilename.substr(0, lastindex);
8378 
8379  /*--- Append iteration number for unsteady cases ---*/
8380 
8381  if (Time_Domain) {
8382 
8383  if ((val_iter >= 0) && (val_iter < 10)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d", val_iter);
8384  if ((val_iter >= 10) && (val_iter < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d", val_iter);
8385  if ((val_iter >= 100) && (val_iter < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d", val_iter);
8386  if ((val_iter >= 1000) && (val_iter < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d", val_iter);
8387  if (val_iter >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d", val_iter);
8388  UnstExt = string(buffer);
8389  }
8390  UnstExt += ext;
8391  UnstFilename.append(UnstExt);
8392 
8393  return UnstFilename;
8394 }
8395 
8396 string CConfig::GetMultizone_FileName(string val_filename, int val_iZone, const string& ext) const {

8398  string multizone_filename = std::move(val_filename);
8399  char buffer[50];
8400 
8401  unsigned short lastindex = multizone_filename.find_last_of('.');
8402  multizone_filename = multizone_filename.substr(0, lastindex);
8403 
8404  if (Multizone_Problem) {
8405  SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
8406  multizone_filename.append(string(buffer));
8407  }
8408 
8409  multizone_filename += ext;
8410  return multizone_filename;
8411 }

8453 string CConfig::GetObjFunc_Extension(string val_filename) const {
8454 
8455  string AdjExt, Filename = std::move(val_filename);
8456 
8457  if (ContinuousAdjoint || DiscreteAdjoint) {
8458 
8459  /*--- Remove filename extension (.dat) ---*/
8460 
8461  unsigned short lastindex = Filename.find_last_of('.');
8462  Filename = Filename.substr(0, lastindex);
8463 
8464  if (nObj==1) {
8465  switch (Kind_ObjFunc[0]) {
8466  case DRAG_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cd"; break;
8467  case LIFT_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cl"; break;
8468  case SIDEFORCE_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_csf"; break;
8469  case INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_invpress"; break;
8470  case INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_invheat"; break;
8471  case MOMENT_X_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmx"; break;
8472  case MOMENT_Y_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmy"; break;
8473  case MOMENT_Z_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmz"; break;
8474  case EFFICIENCY: AdjExt = "_eff"; break;
8475  case EQUIVALENT_AREA: AdjExt = "_ea"; break;
8476  case NEARFIELD_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_nfp"; break;
8477  case FORCE_X_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfx"; break;
8478  case FORCE_Y_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfy"; break;
8479  case FORCE_Z_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfz"; break;
8480  case THRUST_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_ct"; break;
8481  case TORQUE_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cq"; break;
8482  case TOTAL_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_totheat"; break;
8483  case MAXIMUM_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_maxheat"; break;
8484  case AVG_TEMPERATURE: AdjExt = "_avtp"; break;
8485  case FIGURE_OF_MERIT: AdjExt = "_merit"; break;
8486  case BUFFET_SENSOR: AdjExt = "_buffet"; break;
8487  case SURFACE_TOTAL_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_pt"; break;
8488  case SURFACE_STATIC_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_pe"; break;
8489  case SURFACE_STATIC_TEMPERATURE: AdjExt = "_T"; break;
8490  case SURFACE_MASSFLOW: AdjExt = "_mfr"; break;
8491  case SURFACE_UNIFORMITY: AdjExt = "_uniform"; break;
8492  case SURFACE_SECONDARY: AdjExt = "_second"; break;
8493  case SURFACE_MOM_DISTORTION: AdjExt = "_distort"; break;
8494  case SURFACE_SECOND_OVER_UNIFORM: AdjExt = "_sou"; break;
8495  case SURFACE_PRESSURE_DROP: AdjExt = "_dp"; break;
8496  case SURFACE_SPECIES_0: AdjExt = "_avgspec0"; break;
8497  case SURFACE_SPECIES_VARIANCE: AdjExt = "_specvar"; break;
8498  case SURFACE_MACH: AdjExt = "_mach"; break;
8499  case CUSTOM_OBJFUNC: AdjExt = "_custom"; break;
8500  case REFERENCE_GEOMETRY: AdjExt = "_refgeom"; break;
8501  case REFERENCE_NODE: AdjExt = "_refnode"; break;
8502  case VOLUME_FRACTION: AdjExt = "_volfrac"; break;
8503  case TOPOL_DISCRETENESS: AdjExt = "_topdisc"; break;
8504  case TOPOL_COMPLIANCE: AdjExt = "_topcomp"; break;
8505  case STRESS_PENALTY: AdjExt = "_stress"; break;
8506  }
8507  }
8508  else{
8509  AdjExt = "_combo";
8510  }
8511  Filename.append(AdjExt);
8512 
8513  /*--- Lastly, add the .dat extension ---*/
8514  Filename.append(".dat");
8515 
8516  }
8517 
8518  return Filename;
8519 }

8521 unsigned short CConfig::GetContainerPosition(unsigned short val_eqsystem) {
8522 
8523  switch (val_eqsystem) {
8524  case RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS: return FLOW_SOL;
8525  case RUNTIME_TURB_SYS: return TURB_SOL;
8526  case RUNTIME_TRANS_SYS: return TRANS_SOL;
8527  case RUNTIME_SPECIES_SYS: return SPECIES_SOL;
8528  case RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS: return HEAT_SOL;
8529  case RUNTIME_FEA_SYS: return FEA_SOL;
8530  case RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS: return ADJFLOW_SOL;
8531  case RUNTIME_ADJTURB_SYS: return ADJTURB_SOL;
8532  case RUNTIME_ADJSPECIES_SYS:return ADJSPECIES_SOL;
8533  case RUNTIME_ADJFEA_SYS: return ADJFEA_SOL;
8534  case RUNTIME_RADIATION_SYS: return RAD_SOL;
8535  case RUNTIME_MULTIGRID_SYS: return 0;
8536  }
8537  return 0;
8538 }

8552 
8553 void CConfig::SetGlobalParam(MAIN_SOLVER val_solver,
8554  unsigned short val_system) {
8555 
8556  /*--- Set the simulation global time ---*/
8557 
8558  Current_UnstTime = static_cast<su2double>(TimeIter)*Delta_UnstTime;
8559  Current_UnstTimeND = static_cast<su2double>(TimeIter)*Delta_UnstTimeND;
8560 
8561  /*--- Set the solver methods ---*/
8562 
8563  auto SetFlowParam = [&]() {
8564  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
8565  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
8566  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
8567  MUSCL_Flow, NONE);
8568  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
8569  }
8570  };
8571 
8572  auto SetTurbParam = [&]() {
8573  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TURB_SYS) {
8574  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
8575  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
8576  MUSCL_Turb, NONE);
8577  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
8578  }
8579  };
8580 
8581  auto SetHeatParam = [&]() {
8582  if (val_system == RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS) {
8583  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Heat, Kind_Centered_Heat,
8584  Kind_Upwind_Heat, Kind_SlopeLimit_Heat, MUSCL_Heat, NONE);
8585  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Heat);
8586  }
8587  };
8588 
8589  auto SetSpeciesParam = [&]() {
8590  if (val_system == RUNTIME_SPECIES_SYS) {
8591  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Species, Kind_Centered_Species,
8592  Kind_Upwind_Species, Kind_SlopeLimit_Species,
8593  MUSCL_Species, NONE);
8594  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Species);
8595  }
8596  };
8597 
8598  auto SetAdjFlowParam = [&]() {
8599  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {
8600  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow, Kind_Centered_AdjFlow,
8601  Kind_Upwind_AdjFlow, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow,
8602  MUSCL_AdjFlow, NONE);
8603  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
8604  }
8605  };
8606 
8607  switch (val_solver) {
8608  case MAIN_SOLVER::EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_EULER:
8609  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_EULER: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_EULER:
8610  SetFlowParam();
8611  break;
8612  case MAIN_SOLVER::NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::NEMO_NAVIER_STOKES:
8613  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_NAVIER_STOKES:
8614  SetFlowParam();
8615  SetSpeciesParam();
8616  SetHeatParam();
8617  break;
8618  case MAIN_SOLVER::RANS: case MAIN_SOLVER::INC_RANS:
8619  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_RANS: case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_INC_RANS:
8620  SetFlowParam();
8621  SetTurbParam();
8622  SetSpeciesParam();
8623  SetHeatParam();
8624 
8625  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TRANS_SYS) {
8626  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
8627  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
8628  MUSCL_Turb, NONE);
8629  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
8630  }
8631  break;
8632  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_EULER:
8633  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_NAVIER_STOKES:
8634  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_RANS:
8635  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_LES:
8636  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_EULER:
8637  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_NS:
8638  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM_RANS:
8639  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
8640  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_FEM_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
8641  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
8642  MUSCL_Flow, Kind_FEM_Flow);
8643  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_FEM_Flow);
8644  }
8645  break;
8646  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_EULER:
8647  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES:
8648  SetFlowParam();
8649  SetAdjFlowParam();
8650  break;
8651  case MAIN_SOLVER::ADJ_RANS:
8652  SetFlowParam();
8653  SetTurbParam();
8654  SetAdjFlowParam();
8655 
8656  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJTURB_SYS) {
8657  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjTurb, Kind_Centered_AdjTurb,
8658  Kind_Upwind_AdjTurb, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjTurb,
8659  MUSCL_AdjTurb, NONE);
8660  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjTurb);
8661  }
8662  break;
8663  case MAIN_SOLVER::HEAT_EQUATION:
8664  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_HEAT:
8665  if (val_system == RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS) {
8666  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, CENTERED::NONE, UPWIND::NONE, LIMITER::NONE, NONE, NONE);
8667  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Heat);
8668  }
8669  break;
8670 
8671  case MAIN_SOLVER::FEM_ELASTICITY:
8672  case MAIN_SOLVER::DISC_ADJ_FEM:
8673  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FEA_SYS) {
8674  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, CENTERED::NONE, UPWIND::NONE, LIMITER::NONE, NONE, NONE);
8675  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(NONE);
8676  }
8677  break;
8678 
8679  default:
8680  break;
8681  }
8682 }

8705 unsigned short CConfig::GetMarker_Periodic_Donor(const string& val_marker) const {
8706  unsigned short iMarker_PerBound, jMarker_PerBound, kMarker_All;
8707 
8708  /*--- Find the marker for this periodic boundary. ---*/
8709  for (iMarker_PerBound = 0; iMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; iMarker_PerBound++)
8710  if (Marker_PerBound[iMarker_PerBound] == val_marker) break;
8711 
8712  /*--- Find corresponding donor. ---*/
8713  for (jMarker_PerBound = 0; jMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; jMarker_PerBound++)
8714  if (Marker_PerBound[jMarker_PerBound] == Marker_PerDonor[iMarker_PerBound]) break;
8715 
8716  /*--- Find and return global marker index for donor boundary. ---*/
8717  for (kMarker_All = 0; kMarker_All < nMarker_CfgFile; kMarker_All++)
8718  if (Marker_PerBound[jMarker_PerBound] == Marker_All_TagBound[kMarker_All]) break;
8719 
8720  return kMarker_All;
8721 }

8904 bool CConfig::GetVolumetric_Movement() const {
8905  bool volumetric_movement = false;
8906 
8907  if (GetSurface_Movement(AEROELASTIC) ||
8908  GetSurface_Movement(AEROELASTIC_RIGID_MOTION)||
8909  GetSurface_Movement(EXTERNAL) ||
8910  GetSurface_Movement(EXTERNAL_ROTATION)){
8911  volumetric_movement = true;
8912  }
8913 
8914  if (Kind_SU2 == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_DEF ||
8915  Kind_SU2 == SU2_COMPONENT::SU2_DOT ||
8916  DirectDiff)
8917  { volumetric_movement = true;}
8918 
8919  return volumetric_movement;
8920 }

8922 bool CConfig::GetSurface_Movement(unsigned short kind_movement) const {

8924  if (Kind_SurfaceMovement[iMarkerMoving] == kind_movement){
8925  return true;

8927  }
8928  return false;
8929 }

9763 short CConfig::FindInterfaceMarker(unsigned short iInterface) const {
9764 
9765  /*--- The names of the two markers that form the interface. ---*/
9766  const auto& sideA = Marker_ZoneInterface[2*iInterface];
9767  const auto& sideB = Marker_ZoneInterface[2*iInterface+1];
9768  for (unsigned short iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_All; iMarker++) {
9769  /*--- If the marker is sideA or sideB of the interface (order does not matter). ---*/
9770  const auto& tag = Marker_All_TagBound[iMarker];
9771  if ((tag == sideA) || (tag == sideB)) return iMarker;
9772  }
9773  return -1;
9774 }

9776 void CConfig::Tick(double *val_start_time) {

9778 #ifdef PROFILE
9779  *val_start_time = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
9780 #endif
9781 
9782 }
9783 
9784 void CConfig::Tock(double val_start_time, const string& val_function_name, int val_group_id) {
9785 
9786 #ifdef PROFILE
9787 
9788  double val_stop_time = 0.0, val_elapsed_time = 0.0;
9789 
9790  val_stop_time = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
9791 
9792  /*--- Compute the elapsed time for this subroutine ---*/
9793  val_elapsed_time = val_stop_time - val_start_time;
9794 
9795  /*--- Store the subroutine name and the elapsed time ---*/
9796  Profile_Function_tp.push_back(val_function_name);
9797  Profile_Time_tp.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
9798  Profile_ID_tp.push_back(val_group_id);
9799 
9800 #endif
9801 
9802 }
9803 
9804 void CConfig::SetProfilingCSV() {
9805 
9806 #ifdef PROFILE
9807 
9808  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
9809  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
9810 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
9811  SU2_MPI::Comm_rank(SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &rank);
9812  SU2_MPI::Comm_size(SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &size);
9813 #endif
9814 
9815  /*--- Each rank has the same stack trace, so the they have the same
9816  function calls and ordering in the vectors. We're going to reduce
9817  the timings from each rank and extract the avg, min, and max timings. ---*/
9818 
9819  /*--- First, create a local mapping, so that we can extract the
9820  min and max values for each function. ---*/
9821 
9822  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < Profile_Function_tp.size(); i++) {
9823 
9824  /*--- Add the function and initialize if not already stored (the ID
9825  only needs to be stored the first time).---*/
9826  if (Profile_Map_tp.find(Profile_Function_tp[i]) == Profile_Map_tp.end()) {
9827 
9828  vector<int> profile; profile.push_back(i);
9829  Profile_Map_tp.insert(pair<string,vector<int> >(Profile_Function_tp[i],profile));
9830 
9831  } else {
9832 
9833  /*--- This function has already been added, so simply increment the
9834  number of calls and total time for this function. ---*/
9835 
9836  Profile_Map_tp[Profile_Function_tp[i]].push_back(i);
9837 
9838  }
9839  }
9840 
9841  /*--- We now have everything gathered by function name, so we can loop over
9842  each function and store the min/max times. ---*/
9843 
9844  int map_size = 0;
9845  for (map<string,vector<int> >::iterator it=Profile_Map_tp.begin(); it!=Profile_Map_tp.end(); ++it) {
9846  map_size++;
9847  }
9848 
9849  /*--- Allocate and initialize memory ---*/
9850 
9851  double *l_min_red = NULL, *l_max_red = NULL, *l_tot_red = NULL, *l_avg_red = NULL;
9852  int *n_calls_red = NULL;
9853  double* l_min = new double[map_size];
9854  double* l_max = new double[map_size];
9855  double* l_tot = new double[map_size];
9856  double* l_avg = new double[map_size];
9857  int* n_calls = new int[map_size];
9858  for (int i = 0; i < map_size; i++)
9859  {
9860  l_min[i] = 1e10;
9861  l_max[i] = 0.0;
9862  l_tot[i] = 0.0;
9863  l_avg[i] = 0.0;
9864  n_calls[i] = 0;
9865  }
9866 
9867  /*--- Collect the info for each function from the current rank ---*/
9868 
9869  int func_counter = 0;
9870  for (map<string,vector<int> >::iterator it=Profile_Map_tp.begin(); it!=Profile_Map_tp.end(); ++it) {
9871 
9872  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < (it->second).size(); i++) {
9873  n_calls[func_counter]++;
9874  l_tot[func_counter] += Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]];
9875  if (Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]] < l_min[func_counter])
9876  l_min[func_counter] = Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]];
9877  if (Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]] > l_max[func_counter])
9878  l_max[func_counter] = Profile_Time_tp[(it->second)[i]];
9879 
9880  }
9881  l_avg[func_counter] = l_tot[func_counter]/((double)n_calls[func_counter]);
9882  func_counter++;
9883  }
9884 
9885  /*--- Now reduce the data ---*/
9886 
9887  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
9888  l_min_red = new double[map_size];
9889  l_max_red = new double[map_size];
9890  l_tot_red = new double[map_size];
9891  l_avg_red = new double[map_size];
9892  n_calls_red = new int[map_size];
9893  }
9894 
9895 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
9896  MPI_Reduce(n_calls, n_calls_red, map_size, MPI_INT, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9897  MPI_Reduce(l_tot, l_tot_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9898  MPI_Reduce(l_avg, l_avg_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_SUM, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9899  MPI_Reduce(l_min, l_min_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MIN, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9900  MPI_Reduce(l_max, l_max_red, map_size, MPI_DOUBLE, MPI_MAX, MASTER_NODE, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
9901 #else
9902  memcpy(n_calls_red, n_calls, map_size*sizeof(int));
9903  memcpy(l_tot_red, l_tot, map_size*sizeof(double));
9904  memcpy(l_avg_red, l_avg, map_size*sizeof(double));
9905  memcpy(l_min_red, l_min, map_size*sizeof(double));
9906  memcpy(l_max_red, l_max, map_size*sizeof(double));
9907 #endif
9908 
9909  /*--- The master rank will write the file ---*/
9910 
9911  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
9912 
9913  /*--- Take averages over all ranks on the master ---*/
9914 
9915  for (int i = 0; i < map_size; i++) {
9916  l_tot_red[i] = l_tot_red[i]/(double)size;
9917  l_avg_red[i] = l_avg_red[i]/(double)size;
9918  n_calls_red[i] = n_calls_red[i]/size;
9919  }
9920 
9921  /*--- Now write a CSV file with the processed results ---*/
9922 
9923  ofstream Profile_File;
9924  Profile_File.precision(15);
9925  Profile_File.open("profiling.csv");
9926 
9927  /*--- Create the CSV header ---*/
9928 
9929  Profile_File << "\"Function_Name\", \"N_Calls\", \"Avg_Total_Time\", \"Avg_Time\", \"Min_Time\", \"Max_Time\", \"Function_ID\"" << endl;
9930 
9931  /*--- Loop through the map and write the results to the file ---*/
9932 
9933  func_counter = 0;
9934  for (map<string,vector<int> >::iterator it=Profile_Map_tp.begin(); it!=Profile_Map_tp.end(); ++it) {
9935 
9936  Profile_File << scientific << it->first << ", " << n_calls_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_tot_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_avg_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_min_red[func_counter] << ", " << l_max_red[func_counter] << ", " << (int)Profile_ID_tp[(it->second)[0]] << endl;
9937  func_counter++;
9938  }
9939 
9940  Profile_File.close();
9941 
9942  }
9943 
9944  delete [] l_min;
9945  delete [] l_max;
9946  delete [] l_avg;
9947  delete [] l_tot;
9948  delete [] n_calls;
9949  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
9950  delete [] l_min_red;
9951  delete [] l_max_red;
9952  delete [] l_avg_red;
9953  delete [] l_tot_red;
9954  delete [] n_calls_red;
9955  }
9956 
9957 #endif
9958 
9959 }

9961 void CConfig::GEMM_Tick(double *val_start_time) const {

9964 
9965 #ifdef HAVE_MKL
