9974 
9975 void CConfig::GEMM_Tock(double val_start_time, int M, int N, int K) const {
9976 
9977 #ifdef PROFILE
9978 
9979  /* Determine the timing value. The actual function called depends on
9980  the type of executable. */
9981  double val_stop_time = 0.0;
9982 
9983 #ifdef HAVE_MKL
9984  val_stop_time = dsecnd();
9985 #else
9986  val_stop_time = SU2_MPI::Wtime();
9987 #endif
9988 
9989  /* Compute the elapsed time. */
9990  const double val_elapsed_time = val_stop_time - val_start_time;
9991 
9992  /* Create the CLong3T from the M-N-K values and check if it is already
9993  stored in the map GEMM_Profile_MNK. */
9994  CLong3T MNK(M, N, K);
9995  map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI = GEMM_Profile_MNK.find(MNK);
9996 
9997  if(MI == GEMM_Profile_MNK.end()) {
9998 
9999  /* Entry is not present yet. Create it. */
10000  const int ind = GEMM_Profile_MNK.size();
10001  GEMM_Profile_MNK[MNK] = ind;
10002 
10003  GEMM_Profile_NCalls.push_back(1);
10004  GEMM_Profile_TotTime.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
10005  GEMM_Profile_MinTime.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
10006  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.push_back(val_elapsed_time);
10007  }
10008  else {
10009 
10010  /* Entry is already present. Determine its index in the
10011  map and update the corresponding vectors. */
10012  const int ind = MI->second;
10013  ++GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind];
10014  GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind] += val_elapsed_time;
10015  GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind] = min(GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind], val_elapsed_time);
10016  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind] = max(GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind], val_elapsed_time);
10017  }
10018 
10019 #endif
10020 
10021 }
10022 
10023 void CConfig::GEMMProfilingCSV() {
10024 
10025 #ifdef PROFILE
10026 
10027  /* Initialize the rank to the master node. */
10028  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
10029 
10030 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
10031  /* Parallel executable. The profiling data must be sent to the master node.
10032  First determine the rank and size. */
10033  int size;
10034  SU2_MPI::Comm_rank(SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &rank);
10035  SU2_MPI::Comm_size(SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &size);
10036 
10037  /* Check for the master node. */
10038  if(rank == MASTER_NODE) {
10039 
10040  /* Master node. Loop over the other ranks to receive their data. */
10041  for(int proc=1; proc<size; ++proc) {
10042 
10043  /* Block until a message from this processor arrives. Determine
10044  the number of entries in the receive buffers. */
10045  SU2_MPI::Status status;
10046  SU2_MPI::Probe(proc, 0, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
10047 
10048  int nEntries;
10049  SU2_MPI::Get_count(&status, MPI_LONG, &nEntries);
10050 
10051  /* Allocate the memory for the receive buffers and receive the
10052  three messages using blocking receives. */
10053  vector<long> recvBufNCalls(nEntries);
10054  vector<double> recvBufTotTime(nEntries);
10055  vector<double> recvBufMinTime(nEntries);
10056  vector<double> recvBufMaxTime(nEntries);
10057  vector<long> recvBufMNK(3*nEntries);
10058 
10059  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufNCalls.data(), recvBufNCalls.size(),
10060  MPI_LONG, proc, 0, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
10061  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufTotTime.data(), recvBufTotTime.size(),
10062  MPI_DOUBLE, proc, 1, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
10063  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufMinTime.data(), recvBufMinTime.size(),
10064  MPI_DOUBLE, proc, 2, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
10065  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufMaxTime.data(), recvBufMaxTime.size(),
10066  MPI_DOUBLE, proc, 3, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
10067  SU2_MPI::Recv(recvBufMNK.data(), recvBufMNK.size(),
10068  MPI_LONG, proc, 4, SU2_MPI::GetComm(), &status);
10069 
10070  /* Loop over the number of entries. */
10071  for(int i=0; i<nEntries; ++i) {
10072 
10073  /* Create the CLong3T from the M-N-K values and check if it is already
10074  stored in the map GEMM_Profile_MNK. */
10075  CLong3T MNK(recvBufMNK[3*i], recvBufMNK[3*i+1], recvBufMNK[3*i+2]);
10076  map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI = GEMM_Profile_MNK.find(MNK);
10077 
10078  if(MI == GEMM_Profile_MNK.end()) {
10079 
10080  /* Entry is not present yet. Create it. */
10081  const int ind = GEMM_Profile_MNK.size();
10082  GEMM_Profile_MNK[MNK] = ind;
10083 
10084  GEMM_Profile_NCalls.push_back(recvBufNCalls[i]);
10085  GEMM_Profile_TotTime.push_back(recvBufTotTime[i]);
10086  GEMM_Profile_MinTime.push_back(recvBufMinTime[i]);
10087  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.push_back(recvBufMaxTime[i]);
10088  }
10089  else {
10090 
10091  /* Entry is already present. Determine its index in the
10092  map and update the corresponding vectors. */
10093  const int ind = MI->second;
10094  GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind] += recvBufNCalls[i];
10095  GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind] += recvBufTotTime[i];
10096  GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind] = min(GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind], recvBufMinTime[i]);
10097  GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind] = max(GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind], recvBufMaxTime[i]);
10098  }
10099  }
10100  }
10101  }
10102  else {
10103 
10104  /* Not the master node. Create the send buffer for the MNK data. */
10105  vector<long> sendBufMNK(3*GEMM_Profile_NCalls.size());
10106  for(map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI =GEMM_Profile_MNK.begin();
10107  MI!=GEMM_Profile_MNK.end(); ++MI) {
10108 
10109  const int ind = 3*MI->second;
10110  sendBufMNK[ind] = MI->first.long0;
10111  sendBufMNK[ind+1] = MI->first.long1;
10112  sendBufMNK[ind+2] = MI->first.long2;
10113  }
10114 
10115  /* Send the data to the master node using blocking sends. */
10116  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_NCalls.data(), GEMM_Profile_NCalls.size(),
10117  MPI_LONG, MASTER_NODE, 0, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
10118  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_TotTime.data(), GEMM_Profile_TotTime.size(),
10119  MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, 1, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
10120  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_MinTime.data(), GEMM_Profile_MinTime.size(),
10121  MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, 2, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
10122  SU2_MPI::Send(GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.data(), GEMM_Profile_MaxTime.size(),
10123  MPI_DOUBLE, MASTER_NODE, 3, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
10124  SU2_MPI::Send(sendBufMNK.data(), sendBufMNK.size(),
10125  MPI_LONG, MASTER_NODE, 4, SU2_MPI::GetComm());
10126  }
10127 
10128 #endif
10129 
10130  /*--- The master rank will write the file ---*/
10131  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) {
10132 
10133  /* Store the elements of the map GEMM_Profile_MNK in
10134  vectors for post processing reasons. */
10135  const unsigned int nItems = GEMM_Profile_MNK.size();
10136  vector<long> M(nItems), N(nItems), K(nItems);
10137  for(map<CLong3T, int>::iterator MI =GEMM_Profile_MNK.begin();
10138  MI!=GEMM_Profile_MNK.end(); ++MI) {
10139 
10140  const int ind = MI->second;
10141  M[ind] = MI->first.long0;
10142  N[ind] = MI->first.long1;
10143  K[ind] = MI->first.long2;
10144  }
10145 
10146  /* In order to create a nicer output the profiling data is sorted in
10147  terms of CPU time spent. Create a vector of pairs for carrying
10148  out this sort. */
10149  vector<pair<double, unsigned int> > sortedTime;
10150 
10151  for(unsigned int i=0; i<GEMM_Profile_TotTime.size(); ++i)
10152  sortedTime.push_back(make_pair(GEMM_Profile_TotTime[i], i));
10153 
10154  sort(sortedTime.begin(), sortedTime.end());
10155 
10156  /* Open the profiling file. */
10157  ofstream Profile_File;
10158  Profile_File.precision(15);
10159  Profile_File.open("gemm_profiling.csv");
10160 
10161  /* Create the CSV header */
10162  Profile_File << "\"Total_Time\", \"N_Calls\", \"Avg_Time\", \"Min_Time\", \"Max_Time\", \"M\", \"N\", \"K\", \"Avg GFLOPs\"" << endl;
10163 
10164  /* Loop through the different items, where the item with the largest total time is
10165  written first. As sortedTime is sorted in increasing order, the sequence of
10166  sortedTime must be reversed. */
10167  for(vector<pair<double, unsigned int> >::reverse_iterator rit =sortedTime.rbegin();
10168  rit!=sortedTime.rend(); ++rit) {
10169  /* Determine the original index in the profiling vectors. */
10170  const unsigned int ind = rit->second;
10171  const double AvgTime = GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind]/GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind];
10172  const double GFlops = 2.0e-9*M[ind]*N[ind]*K[ind]/AvgTime;
10173 
10174  /* Write the data. */
10175  Profile_File << scientific << GEMM_Profile_TotTime[ind] << ", " << GEMM_Profile_NCalls[ind] << ", "
10176  << AvgTime << ", " << GEMM_Profile_MinTime[ind] << ", " << GEMM_Profile_MaxTime[ind] << ", "
10177  << M[ind] << ", " << N[ind] << ", " << K[ind] << ", " << GFlops << endl;
10178  }
10179 
10180  /* Close the file. */
10181  Profile_File.close();
10182  }
10183 
10184 #endif
10185 
10186 }

10196 void CConfig::SetMultizone(const CConfig *driver_config, const CConfig* const* config_container){
10197 
10198  for (unsigned short iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++){
10199 
10200  if (config_container[iZone]->GetTime_Domain() != GetTime_Domain()){
10201  SU2_MPI::Error("Option TIME_DOMAIN must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10202  }
10203  if (config_container[iZone]->GetnTime_Iter() != GetnTime_Iter()){
10204  SU2_MPI::Error("Option TIME_ITER must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10205  }
10206  if (config_container[iZone]->GetnOuter_Iter() != GetnOuter_Iter()){
10207  SU2_MPI::Error("Option OUTER_ITER must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10208  }
10209  if (config_container[iZone]->GetTime_Step() != GetTime_Step()){
10210  SU2_MPI::Error("Option TIME_STEP must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10211  }
10212  if (config_container[iZone]->GetUnst_CFL() != 0.0){
10213  SU2_MPI::Error("Option UNST_CFL_NUMBER cannot be used in multizone problems (must be 0),"
10214  " use a fixed TIME_STEP instead.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10215  }
10216  if (config_container[iZone]->GetMultizone_Problem() != GetMultizone_Problem()){
10217  SU2_MPI::Error("Option MULTIZONE must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10218  }
10219  if (config_container[iZone]->GetMultizone_Mesh() != GetMultizone_Mesh()){
10220  SU2_MPI::Error("Option MULTIZONE_MESH must be the same in all zones.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10221  }
10222  if(config_container[iZone]->GetWnd_Cauchy_Crit()){
10223  SU2_MPI::Error("Option WINDOW_CAUCHY_CRIT must be deactivated for multizone problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10224  }
10225  }
10226  if(driver_config->GetWnd_Cauchy_Crit()){
10227  SU2_MPI::Error("Option WINDOW_CAUCHY_CRIT must be deactivated for multizone problems.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10228  }
10229 
10230  bool multiblockDriver = false;
10231  for (unsigned short iFiles = 0; iFiles < driver_config->GetnVolumeOutputFiles(); iFiles++){
10232  if (driver_config->GetVolumeOutputFiles()[iFiles] == OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_MULTIBLOCK){
10233  multiblockDriver = true;
10234  }
10235  }
10236 
10237  bool multiblockZone = false;
10238  for (unsigned short iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++){
10239  multiblockZone = false;
10240  for (unsigned short iFiles = 0; iFiles < config_container[iZone]->GetnVolumeOutputFiles(); iFiles++){
10241  if (config_container[iZone]->GetVolumeOutputFiles()[iFiles] == OUTPUT_TYPE::PARAVIEW_MULTIBLOCK){
10242  multiblockZone = true;
10243  }
10244  }
10245  if (multiblockZone != multiblockDriver){
10246  SU2_MPI::Error("To enable PARAVIEW_MULTIBLOCK output, add it to OUTPUT_FILES option in main config and\n"
10247  "remove option from sub-config files.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
10248  }
10249  }
10250 
10251  /*--- Fix the Time Step for all subdomains, for the case of time-dependent problems ---*/
10252  if (driver_config->GetTime_Domain()){
10253  Delta_UnstTime = driver_config->GetTime_Step();
10254 
10255  Time_Domain = true;
10256  }
10257 
10258  /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
10259  /*------ Determine the special properties of the problem -----*/
10260  /*------------------------------------------------------------*/
10261 
10262  bool fluid_zone = false;
10263  bool structural_zone = false;
10264 
10265  /*--- If there is at least a fluid and a structural zone ---*/
10266  for (auto iZone = 0u; iZone < nZone; iZone++) {
10267  fluid_zone |= config_container[iZone]->GetFluidProblem();
10268  structural_zone |= config_container[iZone]->GetStructuralProblem();
10269  }
10270 
10271  if (structural_zone) Relaxation = true;
10272 
10273  /*--- If the problem has FSI properties ---*/
10274  FSI_Problem = fluid_zone && structural_zone;
10275 
10276  Multizone_Residual = true;
10277 }
